\f0\b\fs51\fsmilli25740 \cf3 Chapter I \'96 Authority, Jurisdiction and Social Order\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf3 Article 1: Supremacy of the Federation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Supreme Governing Authority\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Recognition of Supremacy \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This Federation shall be recognized as the Supreme Governing Authority of Earth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Exclusivity of Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No other Government shall possess authority superior to that of this Federation; nor shall any other government be established that replicates the structure or authority of this Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Supremacy of Law\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 This Constitution, and the Laws of Earth which shall be made in Pursuance thereof; and all Treaties made, or which shall be made, under the Authority of the Federation, shall be the supreme Law of the Land; and the Judges in every Nation shall be bound thereby, any Thing in this Constitution or Laws of any Nation to the Contrary notwithstanding.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 2: Public Good and Public Interest\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Obligation of the Federation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Primary Duty\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall, in all its actions and policies, be bound to serve exclusively the Public Good and to act in accordance with the Public Interest.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Definition of Public Good\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 For the purposes of this Constitution, the "Public Good" shall be understood as: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The collective well-being and welfare of all Citizens of the Federation;\
\ls1\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The long-term sustainability and prosperity of the Federation as a whole;\
\ls1\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The protection and advancement of the rights and freedoms enumerated in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Definition of Public Interest\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The "Public Interest" shall be interpreted as: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone That which benefits the Federation and its Citizens as a whole, rather than any particular individual, group, or entity; \
\ls2\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The promotion of justice, equality, and fairness in all aspects of governance and society;\
\ls2\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The preservation and enhancement of the Federation's resources, environment, and cultural heritage for present and future generations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Balancing Competing Interests\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In cases where various public interests may conflict, the Federation shall strive to balance these interests in a manner that maximizes overall public benefit while minimizing harm to any particular segment of society.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Transparency and Accountability\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 To ensure adherence to this obligation: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Federation shall provide clear and accessible explanations for its actions and policies;\
\ls3\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Regular assessments shall be conducted to evaluate the impact of the Federation's actions on the Public Good;\
\ls3\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Citizens shall have the right to challenge actions or policies they believe do not serve the Public Good through appropriate legal and administrative channels.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Entitlement to Social Order\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Fundamental Right\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Person shall be entitled to a social and international order conducive to the full realization of the rights and freedoms enumerated in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Characteristics of the Social Order\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The social and international order referred to in Subsection 1 shall be characterized by: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The rule of Law and equal application of justice;\
\ls4\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Democratic governance and civic participation;\
\ls4\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Economic systems that promote equitable distribution of resources and opportunities;\
\ls4\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Educational systems that foster critical thinking and informed citizenship;\
\ls4\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Healthcare systems that ensure the physical and mental well-being of all Citizens;\
\ls4\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Environmental policies that protect and preserve the natural world;\
\ls4\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(g)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Cultural policies that celebrate diversity and promote mutual understanding.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: International Cooperation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall actively engage in international cooperation to promote a global order that: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Respects the sovereignty of nations;\
\ls5\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Promotes peaceful resolution of conflicts;\
\ls5\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Addresses global challenges such as climate change, poverty, and disease;\
\ls5\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Fosters fair and equitable economic relations between nations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Continuous Improvement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall strive for continuous improvement of the social and international order, adapting to new challenges and opportunities as they arise.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Citizen Participation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Citizens shall have the right and responsibility to contribute to the shaping and maintenance of this social and international order through: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Active participation in democratic processes;\
\ls6\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Engagement in civil society organizations;\
\ls6\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Promotion of social justice and equality in their communities;\
\ls6\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Responsible exercise of their rights and freedoms.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Education and Awareness\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall promote education and awareness about the nature and importance of this social and international order, ensuring that all Citizens understand their role in its realization and maintenance.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Remedies for Violations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall establish effective mechanisms for Citizens to seek redress when they believe the social and international order is not conducive to the full realization of their rights and freedoms.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 3: Credit and Debt\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Full Faith and Credit\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 Full Faith and Credit shall be given in each Nation to the public Acts, Records, and judicial Proceedings of every other Nation. And the Federation may by general Laws prescribe the Manner in which such Acts, Records and Proceedings shall be proved, and the Effect thereof.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Public Debt\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Validity of Public Debt \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The validity of the public debt of the Federation, authorized by Law, including debts incurred for payment of pensions and bounties for services in suppressing insurrection or rebellion, shall not be questioned.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Prohibition on Certain Debts \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Neither the Federation nor any Nation shall assume or pay any debt or obligation incurred in aid of insurrection or rebellion against the Federation; all such debts, obligations and claims shall be held illegal and void.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 4: Reserved Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Principle of Reserved Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Fundamental Principle\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The powers not delegated to the Federation by this Constitution, nor prohibited by it to the Nations, are reserved to the Nations respectively, or to the People thereof.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Purpose\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This principle aims to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Preserve the autonomy and sovereignty of individual Nations within the Federation;\
\ls7\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Limit the scope of the Federation's authority to those powers explicitly granted by this Constitution;\
\ls7\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Ensure that governmental power remains as close to the People as practicable.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Scope of Reserved Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: National Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Reserved powers of the Nations may include, but are not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Regulation of intra-National commerce;\
\ls8\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Establishment and maintenance of educational systems;\
\ls8\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Administration of local law enforcement;\
\ls8\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Management of natural resources within National boundaries;\
\ls8\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Regulation of marriage and family law;\
\ls8\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Administration of elections for National and local offices.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Powers Reserved to the People\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Powers reserved to the People may include, but are not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to petition National governments for redress of grievances;\
\ls9\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to form and participate in local governance structures;\
\ls9\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to engage in economic activities not prohibited by law;\
\ls9\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to cultural and linguistic expression.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Interpretation and Application\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Presumption in Favor of Reserved Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In cases of ambiguity, there shall be a presumption that a power is reserved to the Nations or to the People, unless clearly delegated to the Federation by this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Judicial Review\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Star Court shall have the authority to adjudicate disputes regarding the allocation of powers between the Federation, the Nations, and the People.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Dynamic Interpretation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The interpretation of reserved powers shall evolve to address new circumstances and challenges not foreseen at the time of this Constitution's ratification, while maintaining the core principle of limited Federation authority.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Interaction with Federation Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Concurrent Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In areas where the Federation and Nations have concurrent authority, Federal Law shall be supreme when in direct conflict with National law, but only to the extent necessary to achieve the Federation's constitutionally mandated objectives.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Cooperative Federalism\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation and Nations shall strive for cooperative relationships in areas of shared responsibility, with the Federation providing support and coordination while respecting National autonomy.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Protection of Reserved Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Constitutional Amendments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any proposed amendment to this Constitution that would alter the balance of powers between the Federation, Nations, and People shall require the consent of three-fourths of the Nations, in addition to the standard amendment process.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Federation Overreach\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Nations and Citizens shall have the right to challenge, through appropriate legal channels, any Federation action they believe infringes upon reserved powers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Transparency and Education\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Public Awareness\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation and Nations shall promote public understanding of the reserved powers doctrine through educational programs and regular communications.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Reporting Requirements\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall publish annual reports detailing its use of delegated powers and affirming its respect for reserved powers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section G: Limitations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: No Violation of Fundamental Rights\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Neither the Nations nor the People may exercise reserved powers in a manner that violates the fundamental rights guaranteed by this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Inter-National Harmony\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The exercise of reserved powers by one Nation shall not unduly interfere with the rights or interests of other Nations within the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 5: Limitations on National Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Prohibited Actions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 No Nation shall: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Enter into any Treaty, Alliance, or Confederation;\
\ls10\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Grant Letters of Marque and Reprisal;\
\ls10\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Coin Money; \
\ls10\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Emit Bills of Credit; \
\ls10\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Make any Thing but gold and silver Coin a Tender in Payment of Debts; \
\ls10\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Pass any Bill of Attainder, ex post facto Law, or Law impairing the Obligation of Contracts; or \
\ls10\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(g)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Grant any Title of Nobility.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Actions Requiring Federal Consent\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Imposts and Duties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Nation shall, without the Consent of the Federation, impose any Imposts or Duties on Imports or Exports, except those necessary for enforcing its inspection laws. The net revenue from all Duties and Imposts imposed by any Nation on Imports or Exports shall belong to the Treasury of Earth, and such Laws shall be subject to review and control by the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Other Restricted Actions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Nation shall, without the Consent of the Federation: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Impose any Duty of Tonnage;\
\ls11\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Maintain Troops or Ships of War in time of Peace; \
\ls11\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Enter into any Agreement or Compact with another Nation or extraterrestrial Power; or \
\ls11\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Engage in War, unless actually invaded, or in such imminent Danger as will not admit delay.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 6: Guarantee of Governmental Form and Protection\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Form of Government\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Guarantee \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall guarantee to every Nation within this Union a Democratic-Socialist Form of Government.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Protection Against Threats\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Obligation to Protect \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall protect each Nation against: (a) Invasion; (b) Cyberattacks; and (c) Other similar threats to national security and sovereignty.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Application for Protection \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Upon Application of: (a) The Legislature of a Nation; or (b) The Executive of a Nation, when the Legislature cannot be convened, the Federation shall protect such Nation against Violence.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 7: Prohibition of Slavery and Servitude\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Absolute Prohibition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Prohibition of Slavery and Servitude \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be held in slavery or servitude.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Prohibition of Slave Trade \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Slavery and the slave trade are hereby prohibited in all their forms.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Enforcement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Federation and all Nations shall take all necessary measures to prevent, suppress, and punish any violation of Section A of this Article.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 8: Human Dignity and Equality\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Inherent Human Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 All Persons are hereby recognized as born free and equal in dignity and rights, endowed with reason and conscience, and shall act towards one another in a spirit of kinship.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Legal Recognition and Personal Security \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Equal Recognition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Person shall have the Right to equal recognition as a person before the Law in all jurisdictions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Fundamental Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Person shall have the inalienable Right to life, liberty, and security of person.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Equality Before the Law \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Equal Protection \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All Persons shall be equal before the Law and shall be entitled, without discrimination, to equal protection of the Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Protection Against Discrimination \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All Persons shall be entitled to equal protection against any form of discrimination that violates this Constitution and against any incitement to such discrimination.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 9: Sanctity of Life\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Prohibition of Unlawful Deprivation of Life\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: General Prohibition\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person, including but not limited to any representative, officer, judge, senator, or official of this Federation, shall unlawfully cause or contribute to the death of another individual.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Scope of Prohibition\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This prohibition extends to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Direct actions resulting in death;\
\ls12\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Indirect actions that foreseeably lead to death;\
\ls12\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Negligent acts or omissions that result in death;\
\ls12\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Conspiracy to cause the death of another;\
\ls12\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Aiding or abetting in actions that result in death.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Application to Legal Entities\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The prohibition shall also apply to corporations, organizations, and other legal entities operating within the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Extraterritorial Application\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This prohibition shall apply to actions of Federation officials and citizens both within the territory of the Federation and off planet.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Exceptions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Due Process of Law\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The prohibition in Section A shall not apply to actions permitted under due process of law, as prescribed by statute and in accordance with this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Lawful Exceptions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Lawful exceptions may include, but are not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Self-defense or defense of others from imminent threat of death or severe bodily harm;\
\ls13\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Actions taken by law enforcement officers in the lawful performance of their duties, subject to strict regulations on the use of lethal force;\
\ls13\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Military actions during times of declared war, subject to international Law and the laws of war;\
\ls13\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Medically assisted end-of-life procedures, where permitted by Law and subject to strict safeguards.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Capital Punishment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The imposition of capital punishment, if permitted by law, shall be subject to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls14\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The most rigorous due process protections;\
