\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be held to answer for a capital, or otherwise infamous crime, unless on a presentment or indictment of a Grand Jury, except in cases arising in the land or naval forces, or in the Militia, when in actual service in time of War or public danger.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Double Jeopardy \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be subject for the same offense to be twice put in jeopardy of life or limb.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Self-Incrimination \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be compelled in any criminal case to be a witness against themselves.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Due Process \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be deprived of life, liberty, or property, without due process of Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Extradition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A Person charged in any Nation with Treason, Felony, or other Crime, who shall flee from Justice, and be found in another Nation, shall, on Demand of the Executive Authority of the Nation from which they fled, be delivered up, to be removed to the Nation having Jurisdiction of the Crime.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 12: Veracity in Sworn Testimony\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Prohibition of False Testimony\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: General Prohibition\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall knowingly provide false testimony or make material misrepresentations while under oath or affirmation in any official proceeding, judicial or otherwise, within the jurisdiction of this Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Definition of False Testimony\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 False testimony shall be defined as: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls26\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Making a statement that the person knows to be untrue;\
\ls26\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Denying knowledge of a fact that the person knows to be true;\
\ls26\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Creating a false impression by omitting significant information\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Material Misrepresentation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A misrepresentation shall be considered material if it has the potential to influence the outcome of the proceeding or the decision-making process of the relevant authority.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Intent Requirement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The prohibition applies to statements made with the intent to deceive or mislead, or with reckless disregard for the truth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Scope of Application\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Comprehensive Coverage\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This Article shall apply to all proceedings, including but not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls27\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Court hearings at all levels of the judiciary;\
\ls27\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Legislative inquiries and committee hearings;\
\ls27\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Administrative procedures and regulatory investigations;\
\ls27\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Arbitration and mediation proceedings;\
\ls27\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Sworn affidavits and depositions;\
\ls27\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Grand jury testimonies;\
\ls27\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(g)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Military tribunals and courts-martial.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Jurisdictional Extent\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This Article shall apply to all proceedings within the territorial jurisdiction of the Federation, as well as to testimony given by Citizens of the Federation in international forums or foreign jurisdictions where the Federation has a substantial interest.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Oath or Affirmation Requirement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Administration of Oath\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Before giving testimony in any official proceeding, each witness shall be required to take an oath or make an affirmation to tell the truth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Form of Oath\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The standard form of the oath shall be: "I swear (or affirm) that the testimony I am about to give is the truth, the whole truth, and nothing but the truth, under penalty of Law."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Accommodations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Alternative forms of the oath or affirmation shall be provided to accommodate various religious beliefs or philosophical objections, while maintaining the solemnity and legal significance of the act.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Penalties and Enforcement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Criminal Penalties\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Violation of this Article shall be considered perjury, a serious criminal offense punishable by: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls28\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Imprisonment for a term to be determined by law;\
\ls28\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Substantial fines;\
\ls28\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Both imprisonment and fines.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Civil Penalties\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In addition to criminal penalties, persons who provide false testimony may be subject to civil liability for any damages resulting from their false statements.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Professional Consequences\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 For professionals testifying in their official capacity, violation of this Article may result in: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls29\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Loss of professional licenses or certifications;\
\ls29\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Disbarment or suspension from professional practice;\
\ls29\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Permanent disqualification from holding public office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Impeachment of Testimony\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 False testimony may be used to impeach the credibility of a witness in current or future proceedings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Protections for Witnesses\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Right to Counsel\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Witnesses shall have the right to consult with legal counsel before and during their testimony.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Protection Against Self-Incrimination\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No witness shall be compelled to give testimony that may incriminate themself, in accordance with the protections against self-incrimination provided in Article 11, Section A, Subsection 3 of this Chapter of this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Immunity Provisions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Witnesses may be granted immunity from prosecution in exchange for truthful testimony, subject to conditions and limitations prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Recantation and Correction\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Opportunity to Recant\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A person who has given false testimony shall have the opportunity to recant or correct their testimony without penalty if done: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls30\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone During the same proceeding and before the false testimony has substantially affected the proceeding;\
\ls30\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Within a reasonable time frame as defined by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Mitigation of Penalties\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Voluntary recantation or correction of false testimony, even if not within the time frame specified in Subsection 1, may be considered as a mitigating factor in determining penalties.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section G: Education and Prevention\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Public Awareness\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall promote public awareness of the importance of truthful testimony and the consequences of perjury through educational programs and public information campaigns.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Professional Training\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Legal professionals, law enforcement officers, and others involved in official proceedings shall receive specific training on identifying and preventing false testimony.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section H: Technological Aids\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Use of Technology\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation may employ appropriate technological aids, such as biometric stress detection or advanced forensic techniques, to assist in verifying the truthfulness of testimony, subject to privacy protections and scientific validity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 13: Treason\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Definition of Treason\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Acts Constituting Treason\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Treason against the Federation shall consist only in:\
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls31\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Levying War against the Federation, which includes: \
\pard\tx360\tx785\pardeftab720\li785\fi-786\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls31\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(i)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Actively participating in armed rebellion or insurrection against the Federation's authority;\
\ls31\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(ii)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Organizing or leading forces to overthrow the Federation's government;\
\ls31\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(iii)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Providing material support, such as weapons or strategic intelligence, to those engaged in armed conflict against the Federation.\
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls31\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Adhering to the Enemies of the Federation, giving them Aid and Comfort, which includes:\
\pard\tx360\tx785\pardeftab720\li785\fi-786\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls31\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(i)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Providing intelligence, military secrets, or strategic information to declared enemies of the Federation;\
\ls31\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(ii)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Harboring or concealing agents of enemy powers;\
\ls31\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(iii)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Sabotaging the Federation's military efforts or critical infrastructure during times of declared war or conflict;\
\ls31\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(iv)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Engaging in propaganda activities on behalf of an enemy power during wartime.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Intent Requirement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 To be guilty of treason, a person must act with the specific intent to betray the Federation. Mere negligence or recklessness does not constitute treason.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Enemies of the Federation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 For the purposes of this Article, "Enemies of the Federation" shall be defined as: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls32\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Any nation, organization, or group against which the Federation has declared war;\
\ls32\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Any entity formally designated as an enemy of the Federation by act of the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Evidentiary Requirements\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Conviction Standards\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be convicted of Treason unless on: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls33\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Testimony of two Witnesses to the same overt Act; or\
\ls33\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Confession in open Court.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Overt Act Requirement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The prosecution must prove that the accused committed an overt act of treason. Mere thoughts, intentions, or speech alone, without accompanying action, do not constitute treason.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Corroboration of Confession\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 If conviction is sought based on a confession in open Court, there must be additional corroborating evidence to support the confession.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Limitations and Protections\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Statute of Limitations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 There shall be no statute of limitations for the crime of treason.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Protection of Political Dissent\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Criticism of the Federation's government, policies, or officials, no matter how harsh or unpopular, shall not be considered treason when expressed through legal and peaceful means.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Double Jeopardy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No person shall be tried for treason more than once for the same act or series of related acts.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Penalties\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Maximum Penalty\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The maximum penalty for treason shall be life imprisonment without the possibility of parole.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Prohibition of Corruption of Blood\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Attainder of Treason shall work Corruption of Blood, or Forfeiture except during the Life of the Person attainted.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Jurisdiction and Trial\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Exclusive Jurisdiction\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Star Court shall have exclusive original jurisdiction over all cases of treason against the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Right to Jury Trial\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All persons accused of treason shall have the right to a trial by jury in the Star Court.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 14: Citizenship\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Citizenship\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Acquisition of Citizenship \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All Persons born or naturalized on Earth, and subject to the jurisdiction thereof, shall be Citizens of Earth and concurrently of the Nation wherein they reside.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Protection of Citizens' Rights\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Nation shall enact or enforce any Law which shall abridge the privileges or immunities of Citizens of Earth; nor shall any Nation deprive any person of life, liberty, security, or property, without due process of Law; nor deny to any person within its jurisdiction the equal protection of the Laws.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Uniformity of Citizenship Privileges \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All Citizens of each Nation shall be entitled to all Privileges and Immunities of Citizens of Earth, without distinction or discrimination.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 15: Identification\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Global Identification System\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: DigitalMe ID \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Person, upon birth, shall be entitled to and shall receive an account in a global authentication and identification system, hereinafter referred to as the "DigitalMe ID."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Newborn Registration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The DigitalMe ID shall be issued no later than one (1) month following the date and time of a Person's birth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Security Measures \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The DigitalMe ID shall be secured through robust biometric means, as prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Citizenship Confirmation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Person in possession of a valid DigitalMe ID shall be recognized as a Citizen of Earth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Implementation and Oversight\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Legislative Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall have the power to enact legislation to implement and enforce the provisions of this Article.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Regulatory Body \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall establish, by Law, an independent regulatory body to oversee the implementation and maintenance of the DigitalMe ID system, ensuring its security, privacy, and universal accessibility.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Privacy and Data Protection\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Data Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The use, storage, and transmission of data associated with the DigitalMe ID shall be subject to the data rights and protections enumerated elsewhere in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Mandatory Registration for DigitalMe ID\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Universal Registration Requirement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Person on Earth shall register for and receive a DigitalMe ID within a Period of ten (10) years from the Start Date of the registration program, as established by the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Establishment of Start Date \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall proclaim the Start Date for the DigitalMe ID registration program. This date shall be no later than one (1) year after the ratification of this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Implementation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall, by Law, establish procedures for: (a) The registration process; (b) Verification of identity; (c) Issuance of DigitalMe IDs; (d) Updating and maintaining DigitalMe ID information.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Accessibility \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall ensure that registration facilities and processes are readily accessible to all Persons, including those in remote areas or with limited technological access.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Public Education \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall conduct comprehensive public education campaigns to inform all Persons of the requirement to register for a DigitalMe ID and the procedures for doing so.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Penalties for Non-Compliance \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any Person who fails to register for a DigitalMe ID within the prescribed period shall be subject to penalties as established by Law. Such penalties may include, but are not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls34\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Fines;\
\ls34\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Restrictions on access to certain government services;\
\ls34\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Limitations on participation in certain economic activities;\
\ls34\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Federation shall ensure that penalties are proportionate and do not infringe upon fundamental human rights.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Exceptions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation may, by Law, provide for limited exceptions to the registration requirement for: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls35\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Persons with demonstrable religious or philosophical objections;\
\ls35\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Persons in extreme humanitarian circumstances;\
\ls35\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Other cases as deemed necessary and appropriate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 8: Review and Reporting \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall conduct biennial reviews of the implementation of this Section and shall publish reports on compliance rates, challenges, and measures taken to achieve universal registration.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 \page Article 16: Principles of Democratic Governance and Civic Participation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Right to Participate in Governance\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Fundamental Right \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Citizen of Earth shall possess the inalienable right to participate in the governance of their Nation, either directly or through duly elected representatives.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Modes of Participation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The right enumerated in Subsection 1 shall encompass, but not be limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls36\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to vote in elections and referenda;\
\ls36\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to stand for elected office, subject to qualifications prescribed by Law;\
\ls36\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to petition the government for redress of grievances;\
\ls36\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to participate in public consultations and deliberations on matters of public interest.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Equal Access to Public Service\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Non-Discrimination \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Citizen of Earth shall have the right of equal access to public service within their Nation, without discrimination on any grounds including, but not limited to, race, color, sex, language, religion, political or other opinion, national or social origin, property, birth, or other status.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Merit-Based Selection \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Appointment to public service positions shall be based on merit and qualification, as prescribed by Law, ensuring equal opportunity for all Citizens.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Popular Sovereignty and Electoral Integrity\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Basis of Governmental Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The authority of all Governments, whether National or of the Federation, shall be derived from and dependent upon the will of the People.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Expression of Popular Will\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The will of the People, as referenced in Subsection 1, shall be expressed through periodic and genuine elections, which shall adhere to the following principles: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls37\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Universal and equal suffrage;\
\ls37\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Secret ballot or equivalent free voting procedures that ensure the free expression of the will of the electors;\
\ls37\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Absence of coercion, intimidation, or undue influence in the electoral process.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Frequency of Elections \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Elections shall be held at regular intervals, as prescribed by Law, to ensure the ongoing accountability of elected representatives to the electorate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Implementation and Safeguards\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Electoral Oversight \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall establish, by Law, an independent electoral commission to oversee and ensure the integrity of electoral processes throughout the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Judicial Review \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Star Court as established by Law shall have the authority to adjudicate disputes arising from the implementation of this Article, ensuring adherence to the principles herein enumerated.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 17: Civic Responsibilities and Duties of Citizens\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: General Principles\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Reciprocity of Rights and Duties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Citizen of Earth, by virtue of their citizenship and the rights conferred upon them by this Constitution, shall bear certain responsibilities and duties to the Federation, to society, and to themselves.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Essential Nature of Civic Duties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The fulfillment of the responsibilities and duties enumerated herein shall be deemed essential to the maintenance of a just, equitable, and flourishing society within the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Duties to the Federation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Enumerated Duties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Citizen shall: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls38\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Bear true allegiance to the Federation and uphold this Constitution;\
\ls38\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Obey all lawful orders issued by the authorities of the Federation and comply with the Laws enacted pursuant to this Constitution;\
\ls38\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Defend the Federation against all enemies, extraterrestrial and domestic, when lawfully called upon to do so;\
\ls38\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Contribute to the Federation's welfare through the payment of such taxes as may be lawfully imposed;\
\ls38\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Participate in the democratic processes of the Federation, including but not limited to exercising their right to vote in elections and referenda.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 \page \pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Section C: Responsibilities to Society\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Societal Obligations \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Citizen shall: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls39\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Respect the rights and freedoms of other Citizens as enumerated in this Constitution;\
\ls39\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Contribute to the common good through active participation in community affairs and voluntary service;\
\ls39\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Strive to promote social harmony and mutual understanding among all members of society;\
\ls39\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Protect and preserve the natural environment for present and future generations;\
\ls39\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Report any violations of Law or threats to public safety to the appropriate authorities.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Duties to Oneself\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Personal Development \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Citizen shall: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls40\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Pursue education and self-improvement to the best of their abilities and circumstances;\
\ls40\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Maintain their physical and mental health to the extent reasonably possible;\
\ls40\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Engage in productive activities that contribute to their own well-being and that of society;\
\ls40\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Exercise their rights and freedoms responsibly and with due regard for the rights of others.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Civic Participation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Encouraged Activities \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Citizens are encouraged to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls41\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Actively engage in public discourse on matters of societal importance;\
\ls41\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Seek and disseminate accurate information to promote informed decision-making;\
\ls41\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Participate in local and global initiatives aimed at advancing the welfare of the Federation and its inhabitants.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Limitations and Enforcement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Preservation of Constitutional Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The duties and responsibilities enumerated in this Article shall not be construed as to abrogate or diminish any rights guaranteed in Chapter VIII and Chapter IX of this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Protection of Fundamental Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Citizen shall be compelled by Law to perform any duty or responsibility herein described in a manner that violates their fundamental rights or sincere beliefs, except as may be necessary in times of dire emergency or as explicitly provided for in Chapter VIII and Chapter IX of this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Legislative Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall have the power to enact legislation to promote and facilitate the fulfillment of the duties and responsibilities described in this Article, provided that such legislation does not infringe upon the fundamental rights of Citizens.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Judicial Review \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall have the authority to review any legislation enacted pursuant to Subsection 3 to ensure its compliance with this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 18: Principle of Reciprocal Consideration\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Obligation of Mutual Respect\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: General Principle \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All Persons within the jurisdiction of this Federation shall be obligated to accord to others the same degree of consideration, respect, and kindness that they would reasonably desire for themselves.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Scope of Application \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This principle shall apply to all interactions between individuals, groups, and institutions, including but not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls42\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Personal relationships;\
\ls42\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Professional and business dealings;\
\ls42\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Civic and community engagements;\
\ls42\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Interactions with government officials and institutions;\
\ls42\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Online and digital communications.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Elements of Reciprocal Consideration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The obligation of mutual respect shall include, but not be limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls43\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Treating others with dignity and courtesy;\
\ls43\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Respecting the physical and emotional boundaries of others;\
\ls43\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Acknowledging and respecting diverse viewpoints and life experiences;\
\ls43\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Refraining from actions or speech that would cause unnecessary harm or distress to others;\
\ls43\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Engaging in good faith efforts to understand and accommodate the reasonable needs of others.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Implementation and Enforcement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Education and Promotion \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation and its constituent Nations shall: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls44\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Incorporate the principle of reciprocal consideration into educational curricula at all levels;\
\ls44\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Conduct public awareness campaigns to promote understanding and application of this principle;\
\ls44\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Provide resources and training to help individuals and organizations implement this principle in various contexts.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Institutional Policies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All public institutions and private entities operating within the Federation shall be required to adopt policies that promote and implement the principle of reciprocal consideration.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Dispute Resolution \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Mechanisms shall be established for the peaceful resolution of conflicts arising from alleged violations of this principle, including mediation and restorative justice approaches.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Legal Enforcement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 While primarily aspirational, egregious or persistent violations of this principle may be subject to legal sanction as prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Limitations and Protections\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Reasonable Person Standard \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The obligation set forth in Section A shall be interpreted according to a "reasonable person" standard, taking into account cultural norms and individual circumstances.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Freedom of Expression \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This principle shall not be construed to unduly limit freedom of expression, including the right to engage in robust debate and criticism on matters of public interest.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Self-Defense and Protection of Others \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Nothing in this Article shall be interpreted to prevent individuals from taking reasonable actions to defend themselves or others from imminent harm.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Professional Duties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In professional contexts where individuals have specific ethical or legal obligations (e.g., lawyers, doctors, law enforcement), those obligations shall take precedence where they conflict with this principle.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Public Safety and National Security \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Actions necessary for the maintenance of public safety or national security, when conducted in accordance with Law, shall not be considered violations of this principle.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Interpretation and Application\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Contextual Consideration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In applying this principle, due consideration shall be given to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls45\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The nature and context of the interaction; \
\ls45\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Power dynamics between the parties involved;\
\ls45\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Historical and systemic inequalities that may affect interpersonal dynamics.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Balancing of Interests \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Where the application of this principle conflicts with other rights or obligations, a careful balancing of interests shall be undertaken, with the aim of maximizing mutual respect and consideration.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Continuous Evolution \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The understanding and application of this principle shall evolve over time to reflect changing social norms and values, subject to the fundamental rights and principles enshrined in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Relationship to Other Constitutional Provisions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Complementarity \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This Article shall be interpreted in harmony with other provisions of this Constitution, particularly those relating to fundamental rights, non-discrimination, and social justice.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Non-Derogation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Nothing in this Article shall be construed to derogate from any other rights or freedoms guaranteed by this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 19: Non-Discrimination and Universal Entitlement\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Prohibition of Discrimination \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 Equality of rights under the Law shall not be denied or abridged by the Federation or by any Nation on account of any status.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Universal Entitlement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Scope of Entitlement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Person shall be entitled to all rights and freedoms set forth in this Constitution, without distinction of any kind, including but not limited to distinctions based on race, color, sex, language, religion, political or other opinion, national or social origin, property, birth, or other status.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Non-Discrimination Based on Political Status \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No distinction shall be made on the basis of the political, jurisdictional, or international status of the country or territory to which a Person belongs, whether it be independent, trust, non-self-governing, or under any other limitation of sovereignty.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 20: Prohibition of Discriminatory Conduct\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Proscribed Actions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: General Prohibition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall engage in, promote, condone, or abet any act or expression of hatred, contempt, or unwarranted discrimination directed towards the identity, inherent characteristics, or lawfully protected status of another Person or group of Persons.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Forms of Prohibited Conduct \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Prohibited conduct under this Article shall include, but not be limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls46\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Verbal abuse, including hate speech, slurs, or derogatory language;\
\ls46\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Physical violence or threats thereof;\
\ls46\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Harassment, including sexual harassment;\
\ls46\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Discrimination in employment, housing, education, or access to public services;\
\ls46\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Incitement to discrimination, hostility, or violence;\
\ls46\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Creation or distribution of propaganda promoting hatred or discrimination; \
\ls46\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(g)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Denial of goods or services based on protected characteristics;\
\ls46\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(h)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Exclusion from social, cultural, or political participation based on protected characteristics.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Intent and Effect \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Both intentional acts of discrimination and those with discriminatory effects shall be prohibited; Ignorance of the Law or lack of intent to discriminate shall not be a defense for actions that have discriminatory effects.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Public and Private Sphere \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This prohibition shall apply to both public and private acts, including those committed by individuals, organizations, and governmental entities.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Scope of Protection\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Protected Characteristics \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The protection afforded by Section A shall extend to, but not be limited to, characteristics such as: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Race, color, national or ethnic origin;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Sex, gender identity, and sexual orientation;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Age;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Disability, whether physical or mental;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Religion or belief, including the absence of religious belief;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Social status, including caste, class, or economic condition;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(g)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Marital or family status;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(h)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Genetic information;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(i)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Political opinion or affiliation;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(j)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Language;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(k)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Citizenship or immigration status;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(l)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Pregnancy or parental status;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(m)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Veteran status;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(n)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Physical appearance;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(o)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Educational background;\
\ls47\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(p)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Criminal record.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Intersectionality \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This Article recognizes that individuals may face multiple, intersecting forms of discrimination based on combinations of protected characteristics, and such compounded discrimination shall be specifically addressed in the application of this Article.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Evolving Nature of Protected Characteristics \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The list of protected characteristics shall be subject to periodic review and may be expanded by Law to reflect evolving societal understanding and emergent forms of discrimination.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Exceptions and Limitations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Legitimate Differentiation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This Article does not prohibit legitimate differentiation based on relevant criteria where such differentiation serves a legitimate purpose and is proportionate to that purpose.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Affirmative Action \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Measures designed to achieve substantive equality for disadvantaged groups shall not be considered discrimination under this Article, provided they are temporary and proportionate to the aim pursued.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Enforcement and Remedies\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Legal Prohibition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall enact legislation to give effect to the provisions of this Article, including civil and criminal penalties for violations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Enforcement Bodies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 An independent commission shall be established to investigate complaints, enforce anti-discrimination laws, and promote equality.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Access to Justice \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All Persons shall have access to effective remedies for violations of this Article, including legal aid where necessary.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Burden of Proof \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In civil proceedings related to discrimination, if the complainant establishes facts from which discrimination may be presumed, the burden of proof shall shift to the respondent to prove non-discrimination.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Education and Prevention\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Public Awareness \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation and its constituent Nations shall conduct ongoing public education campaigns to promote understanding, tolerance, and respect for diversity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Educational Curricula \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Anti-discrimination principles and the value of diversity shall be incorporated into educational curricula at all levels.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Training Programs \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Mandatory anti-discrimination training shall be implemented for all public officials and encouraged in private sector organizations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Monitoring and Reporting\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Data Collection \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall collect and publish disaggregated data on discrimination and equality to inform policy-making and measure progress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Periodic Review \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall conduct a comprehensive review of the state of discrimination and the effectiveness of anti-discrimination measures every five years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa427\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs51\fsmilli25740 \cf3 Chapter II \'96 International Legislature\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf3 Article 1: Vesting of Legislative Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Establishment of the World Congress\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Bicameral Legislature \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 There shall be established an international legislative body, hereinafter referred to as the "World Congress," which shall consist of two chambers: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls48\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The House of Representatives; and\
\ls48\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Senate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Grant of Legislative Authority\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Vesting of Powers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All legislative Powers of the Federation granted by this Constitution shall be vested in the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Scope of Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The legislative Powers vested in the World Congress shall extend to all matters within the jurisdiction of the Federation, as defined and limited by this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Exclusivity of Legislative Function\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Sole Legislative Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No other body or entity shall exercise the legislative Powers granted to the World Congress, except as expressly provided for in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Limitations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Constitutional Constraints \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall exercise its legislative Powers subject to the limitations and in accordance with the procedures set forth in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Delegation of Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Prohibition on Abdication \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress may not abdicate or transfer its essential legislative Powers to any other branch of government or external entity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Permissible Delegation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress may, by Law, delegate specific rule-making authority to executive agencies or other bodies, provided that such delegation includes clear guidelines and is subject to legislative oversight.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 2: House of Representatives \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Composition, Election, and Terms of Representatives\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Composition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The House of Representatives of Earth shall be composed of Members apportioned among the Nations as prescribed in Section C of this Article.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Method of Election \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Representatives shall be chosen by the People of Earth from their respective Nations through a ranked-choice election.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Elector Qualifications \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Electors in each Nation shall have the Qualifications requisite for Electors of the most numerous Chamber of the International Legislature.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Term of Office \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Representative shall be elected for a term of 2 years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Reapportionment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Following each decennial census as prescribed in Section C, Subsection 5, the apportionment of Representatives shall be readjusted in accordance with the formula and principles set forth in Section C.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Qualifications\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Age Requirements \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Minimum Age: No Person shall be a Representative who has not attained the age of eighteen (18) years at the time of election; Maximum Age: No Person shall be eligible to assume or retain the office of Representative after having attained the age of sixty-five (65) years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Citizenship and Residency \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be a Representative who is not: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls49\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A Citizen of Earth; and\
\ls49\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone At the time of election, an Inhabitant of the Nation in which they shall be chosen.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Duration of Residency \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be eligible for the office of Representative unless they have been an Inhabitant of the Nation in which they seek election for a period of not less than two (2) years immediately preceding the date of election.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Continuation of Eligibility \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A Representative shall be deemed to have ceased to be an Inhabitant of the Nation from which they were elected if they cease to reside therein during their term of office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Exclusive Allegiance \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be eligible for the office of Representative who holds dual citizenship or owes allegiance to any entity other than Earth and the Nation they seek to represent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Disqualifications \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The following Persons shall be ineligible to hold the office of Representative: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls50\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Persons convicted of treason against the Federation, unless pardoned;\
\ls50\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Persons under impeachment, indictment, or information for any crime punishable by imprisonment for a term exceeding one year;\
\ls50\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Persons adjudged mentally incompetent by a court of competent jurisdiction, unless such judgment has been rescinded.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Apportionment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Composition and Maximum Size\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The House of Representatives shall be composed of no more than one thousand (1000) Members, apportioned among the Nations as follows:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Minimum Representation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Nation shall be allocated a minimum of one (1) Representative.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Maximum Representation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Nation shall have more than forty (40) Representatives.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Apportionment Principle\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The remaining Representatives shall be apportioned among the Nations according to their respective populations, using a logarithmic scale as prescribed by Law, with the aim of providing fair representation while preventing any single Nation or small group of Nations from holding a majority of seats.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Census Requirement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The actual enumeration of population shall be made every five (5) years, in such manner as the World Congress shall by Law direct.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Congressional Authority for Apportionment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish and maintain a formula for apportionment that adheres to these principles and adjusts for changes in global population and the number of Member Nations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Apportionment Formula\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The number of Representatives allocated to each Nation shall be determined by the following formula:\
R = 1 + floor(ln(P / 500,000))\
Where: R is the number of Representatives allocated; P is the population of the Nation as determined by the most recent census; ln denotes the natural logarithm function; floor denotes the mathematical function that rounds down to the nearest integer.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 8: Formula Constraints\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Provided, however, that no Nation shall have fewer than one (1) Representative or more than forty (40) Representatives, regardless of the result of this formula.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 9: Adjustment Authority\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall have the power to adjust the base population number (500,000 in the formula above) by Law to ensure fair representation as global population changes over time.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Vacancies\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Causes of Vacancy \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A vacancy in the House of Representatives may occur due to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls51\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Resignation of a Representative;\
\ls51\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Death of a Representative;\
\ls51\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Expulsion of a Representative by a two-thirds vote of the House;\
\ls51\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Incapacitation of a Representative as determined by procedures established by law;\
\ls51\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Acceptance by a Representative of an office incompatible with the representative mandate, as defined by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Notification of Vacancy \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Executive Authority of the Nation affected shall, within 24 hours of becoming aware of a vacancy, officially notify: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls52\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Speaker of the House of Representatives;\
\ls52\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Premier of Earth;\
\ls52\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Steward of the Public Square;\
\ls52\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The chief election officer of the affected Nation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Issuance of Writs of Election \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Upon notification of a vacancy, the Executive Authority of the affected Nation shall, within 7 days, issue digital writs of election to fill such vacancy; The writs shall specify the date of the special election, which shall be held within 90 days of the vacancy occurring, unless such vacancy happens within 180 days before a regular election for that seat.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Conduct of Special Elections \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Special elections shall be conducted in accordance with the laws of the respective Nation, subject to the provisions of this Constitution; The election process shall ensure equal opportunity for all eligible candidates and maintain the integrity of the electoral system.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Term of Elected Representative \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A Representative elected to fill a vacancy shall serve only for the remainder of the term for which their predecessor was elected.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Continuity of Representation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No district shall be without representation in the House for a period exceeding 120 days, except in cases of force majeure as defined by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Multiple Vacancies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In the event of multiple simultaneous vacancies from a single Nation, the Executive Authority may consolidate special elections to fill these vacancies, provided this does not unduly delay representation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Speaker of the House of Representatives and Other Positions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Election of the Speaker \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The House of Representatives shall, at the beginning of each new Congress, elect from among its members a Speaker of the House; The election shall be by open ballot and shall require an absolute majority of all Representatives; If no candidate achieves an absolute majority in the first round, subsequent rounds of voting shall be held until a Speaker is elected.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Duties of the Speaker \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Speaker of the House shall: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls53\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Preside over sessions of the House of Representatives;\
\ls53\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Ensure the observance of rules and procedures;\
\ls53\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Represent the House in its relations with other branches of government and external entities;\
\ls53\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Determine the legislative calendar in consultation with other House leaders; \
\ls53\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Perform such other duties as may be prescribed by Law or House rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Term of Office for the Speaker \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Speaker shall serve for the duration of the Congress in which they are elected; A Representative may serve as Speaker for multiple terms if so elected.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Removal of the Speaker \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Speaker may be removed from office by a two-thirds vote of all Representatives, following procedures established in the House rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Other Leadership Positions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The House shall elect the following additional officers: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls54\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A Deputy Speaker, who shall act in the absence of the Speaker;\
\ls54\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A Majority Leader and a Minority Leader;\
\ls54\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A Secretary, responsible for maintaining House records and supervising administrative staff;\
\ls54\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A Sergeant-at-Arms, responsible for maintaining order and security;\
\ls54\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Such other officers as the House may deem necessary.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Election and Terms of Other Officers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Other officers shall be elected by a simple majority of Representatives present and voting; They shall serve for the duration of the Congress in which they are elected; They may be removed by a majority vote of all Representatives.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Non-Representative Officers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The positions of Secretary and Sergeant-at-Arms, and other administrative positions as determined by House rules, may be filled by non-Representatives.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 8: Officer Vacancies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any vacancy occurring in the offices established under this Section shall be filled in the same manner as the original election, and the new officer shall serve for the remainder of the original term.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 9: Power of Impeachment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The House of Representatives shall have the sole Power of Impeachment; Articles of Impeachment against any civil Officer of the Federation may be introduced by any member of the House; The adoption of Articles of Impeachment shall require a majority vote of the House; Upon adoption of Articles of Impeachment, the matter shall be referred to the Senate for trial.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 10: Rules and Procedures \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The House of Representatives shall establish its own rules for the election and functioning of its officers and the exercise of its powers, consistent with this Constitution and applicable laws.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 3: Senate\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Composition and Election\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Composition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Senate of Earth shall be composed of three (3) Senators from each Nation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Method of Appointment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Senators shall be appointed by the Legislature of the Nation they represent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Term of Office \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Senator shall be appointed for a term not exceeding six (6) years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Voting Power \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Senator shall have one (1) vote in the Senate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Elector Qualifications \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Electors in each Nation shall have the Qualifications requisite for Electors of the second most numerous Chamber of the International Legislature.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Qualifications for Senators\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Age Requirements \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Minimum Age: No Person shall be a Senator who has not attained the age of twenty-one (21) years at the time of appointment; Maximum Age: No Person shall be eligible to assume or retain the office of Senator after having attained the age of sixty-five (65) years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Citizenship and Residency \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be a Senator who is not: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls55\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A Citizen of Earth; and \
\ls55\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone At the time of appointment, an Inhabitant of the Nation which they shall represent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Duration of Residency \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be eligible for the office of Senator unless they have been an Inhabitant of the Nation they seek to represent for a period of not less than eight (8) years immediately preceding the date of appointment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Apportionment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 Senators shall be apportioned among all Nations within this Union equally, with each Nation entitled to three (3) Senators.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Classification and Rotation of Senators\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Initial Classification \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Immediately subsequent to the first Election, the Senators shall be divided as equally as may be into three Classes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Rotation Schedule \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Seats of Senators of the first Class shall be vacated at the Expiration of the second year; The Seats of Senators of the second Class at the Expiration of the fourth year; and The Seats of Senators of the third Class at the Expiration of the sixth year.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Subsequent Elections \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 One-third of the Senators shall be chosen every second year.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Vacancies\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Causes of Vacancy \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A vacancy in the Senate may occur due to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls56\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Resignation of a Senator;\
\ls56\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Death of a Senator;\
\ls56\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Expulsion of a Senator by a two-thirds vote of the Senate;\
\ls56\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Incapacitation of a Senator as determined by procedures established by law;\
\ls56\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Acceptance by a Senator of an office incompatible with the senatorial mandate, as defined by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Notification of Vacancy \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Executive Authority of the Nation affected shall, within 24 hours of becoming aware of a vacancy, officially notify: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls57\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The President of the Senate;\
\ls57\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Premier of Earth;\
\ls57\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Steward of the Public Square;\
\ls57\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Legislature of the affected Nation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Temporary Appointments \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 If a vacancy occurs during the Recess of the Legislature of any Nation: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls58\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Executive Authority thereof may make a temporary appointment to fill the vacancy;\
\ls58\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Such appointment shall be made within 14 days of the vacancy occurring;\
\ls58\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The appointee must meet all qualifications for the office of Senator as outlined in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Duration of Temporary Appointments \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A temporary appointment shall expire upon the election of a permanent replacement by the Nation's Legislature; In no case shall a temporary appointment extend beyond the end of the next meeting of the Nation's Legislature.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Powers of Temporary Appointees \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Senators appointed temporarily under this Section shall have all the powers and responsibilities of elected Senators.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Permanent Filling of Vacancies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 At its next meeting following a vacancy, the Legislature of the affected Nation shall elect a permanent replacement to fill the vacancy; Such election shall take place within thirty (30) days of the Legislature convening; The elected Senator shall serve for the remainder of the original term.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Special Elections \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 If more than eighteen (18) months remain in the term of the vacant seat, the Nation's Legislature may opt to hold a special election to fill the vacancy, according to procedures established by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 8: Continuity of Representation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Nation shall be without full representation in the Senate for a period exceeding forty-five (45) days, except in cases of force majeure as defined by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Officers of the Senate\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Election of the President of the Senate \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Senate shall, at the beginning of each session, elect from among its members a President of the Senate; The election shall be by secret ballot and shall require an absolute majority of all Senators; If no candidate achieves an absolute majority in the first round, a run-off shall be held between the two candidates receiving the most votes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Duties of the President of the Senate \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The President of the Senate shall: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls59\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Preside over sessions of the Senate;\
\ls59\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Ensure the observance of rules and procedures;\
\ls59\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Represent the Senate in its relations with other branches of government and external entities;\
\ls59\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Perform such other duties as may be prescribed by Law or Senate rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Term of Office for the President \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The President of the Senate shall serve for a term of two years; No Senator shall serve as President for more than two consecutive terms.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Removal of the President \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The President of the Senate may be removed from office by a two-thirds vote of all Senators, following procedures established in the Senate rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Other Officers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Senate shall elect the following additional officers: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls60\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A Vice President, who shall act in the absence of the President;\
\ls60\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A Secretary, responsible for maintaining Senate records and supervising administrative staff;\
\ls60\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A Sergeant-at-Arms, responsible for maintaining order and security;\
\ls60\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Such other officers as the Senate may deem necessary.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Election and Terms of Other Officers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Other officers shall be elected by a simple majority of Senators present and voting; They shall serve for terms of two years, concurrent with the President of the Senate; They may be removed by a majority vote of all Senators.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Non-Senator Officers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The positions of Secretary and Sergeant-at-Arms, and other administrative positions as determined by Senate rules, may be filled by non-Senators.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 8: Officer Vacancies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any vacancy occurring in the offices established under this Section shall be filled in the same manner as the original election, and the new officer shall serve for the remainder of the original term.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 9: Rules and Procedures \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Senate shall establish its own rules for the election and functioning of its officers, consistent with this Constitution and applicable laws.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section G: Impeachment Trials\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Power to Try Impeachments \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Senate shall have the sole Power to try all Impeachments.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Oath or Affirmation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 When sitting for that Purpose, Senators shall be on Oath or Affirmation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Presiding Officer \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 When the Premier of Earth is tried, the Chief Justice of the Star Court shall preside.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Conviction \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be convicted without the Concurrence of two-thirds (2/3) of the Members present.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Judgment in Cases of Impeachment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Judgment in Cases of Impeachment shall not extend further than to removal from Office, and disqualification to hold and enjoy any Office of honor, Trust or Profit under the Federation; The Party convicted shall nevertheless be liable and subject to Indictment, Trial, Judgment and Punishment, according to Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 4: General Elections\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Authority to Regulate Elections\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: National Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Legislature of each Nation shall prescribe the Times, Places, and Manner of holding Elections for Senators and Representatives.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Congressional Override \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Notwithstanding Subsection 1, the World Congress shall have the power, at any time, to make or alter such Regulations by Law, except as to the Places of choosing Representatives and Senators, which shall remain within the exclusive purview of the Nations.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 5: Assemblage, Disqualification and Oath of Office\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Mandatory Annual Session\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Frequency of Assemblage \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall convene in session no less than once per annum.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Designated Commencement Date \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The annual session shall commence on the first Monday of December, unless an alternative date is established by duly enacted legislation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Disqualification from Office\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Scope of Disqualification \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No individual shall be eligible to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls61\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Serve as a Senator or Representative in the World Congress; or \
\ls61\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Hold any office, whether civil or military, under the authority of the Federation or any Nation thereof, if such individual, having previously sworn an oath to support the Constitution of Earth in any of the following capacities:\
\pard\tx360\tx785\pardeftab720\li785\fi-786\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls61\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(i)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone As a member of the World Congress;\
\ls61\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(ii)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone As an officer of the Federation;\
\ls61\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(iii)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone As a member of any National legislature; or \
\ls61\ilvl1\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(iv)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone As an executive or judicial officer of any Nation, shall have subsequently:\
\pard\tx720\tx1145\pardeftab720\li1145\fi-1146\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls61\ilvl2\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(1)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Engaged in insurrection or rebellion against the Federation; or \
\ls61\ilvl2\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(2)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Provided aid or comfort to the enemies of the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Removal of Disqualification \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress may, by a concurrent resolution passed by a two-thirds (2/3) majority in each Chamber, remove the disqualification imposed by Subsection 1 with respect to any individual or class of individuals.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Oath of Office and Prohibition of Religious Tests\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Mandatory Oath or Affirmation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All Senators and Representatives of the World Congress, Members of the various National Legislatures, and all executive and judicial Officers, whether of the Federation or of any Nation thereof, shall be bound by Oath or Affirmation to support this Constitution prior to assuming their respective offices.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Prohibition of Religious Tests\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No religious test shall ever be required as a qualification for any Office or public Trust under the authority of the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Prescribed Oath or Affirmation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Prior to the commencement of their official duties, each person specified in Subsection 1 of this Section shall take the following Oath or Affirmation:\
"I, [state name], do solemnly swear (or affirm) that I will support and defend the Constitution of Earth against all enemies, alien and domestic; that I will bear true faith and allegiance to the same; that I take this obligation freely, without any mental reservation or purpose of evasion; and that I will well and faithfully discharge the duties of the office on which I am about to enter. So help me Sol."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Administration of Oath\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, prescribe the manner in which the Oath or Affirmation shall be administered, and designate the officials authorized to administer such Oath or Affirmation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Record Keeping\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A record of each Oath or Affirmation taken under this Section shall be preserved in such manner as the World Congress shall, by Law, direct.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Penalty for False Oath\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any person who shall take the Oath or Affirmation prescribed herein and subsequently be found to have done so falsely or with intent to evade its obligations shall be subject to such penalties as the World Congress shall, by Law, establish.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 6: Procedural Rules and Operations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: General Rules and Quorum\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Judging Qualifications and Elections \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Chamber of the World Congress shall be the sole Judge of the Elections, Returns, and Qualifications of its own Members.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Quorum \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A Majority of each Chamber shall constitute a Quorum to conduct Business.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Absence of Quorum \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In the absence of a Quorum: (a) A smaller Number may adjourn from day to day; (b) A smaller Number may be authorized to compel the Attendance of absent Members, in such Manner and under such Penalties as each Chamber may provide by its Rules.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Rules of Proceedings \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Chamber may determine the Rules of its Proceedings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Disciplinary Actions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Chamber may: (a) Punish its Members for disorderly Behavior; (b) With the Concurrence of two-thirds (2/3) of its Members, expel a Member.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Journal of Proceedings\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Maintenance of Journal \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Chamber shall keep a Journal of its Proceedings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Publication \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Chamber shall, from time to time, publish its Journal, excepting such Parts as may, in their Judgment, require Secrecy.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Recording of Votes \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Yeas and Nays of the Members of either Chamber on any question shall, at the Desire of one-fifth (1/5) of those Present, be entered on the Journal.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Adjournment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Limitations on Adjournment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Neither Chamber, during the Session of the World Congress, shall, without the Consent of the other Chamber: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls62\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Adjourn for more than three (3) days; or \
\ls62\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Adjourn to any Place other than that in which the two Chambers shall be sitting.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Disagreement on Adjournment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In case of Disagreement between the two Chambers with respect to the Time of Adjournment, the Premier may adjourn them to such Time as the Premier shall think proper, subject to the limitations prescribed Chapter III, Article 6, Section B, Subsection 2 of this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 7: Rights, Privileges, and Restrictions of Members of the World Congress\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Compensation and Privileges\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Compensation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Senators and Representatives shall receive a Compensation for their Services, to be ascertained by Law, and paid out of the Federal Reserve.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Privilege from Arrest \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Except in cases of Treason, Felony, and Breach of the Peace, Members shall be privileged from Arrest during their Attendance at the Session of their respective Chambers, and in going to and returning from the same.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Freedom of Speech and Debate \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 For any Speech or Debate in either Chamber, Members shall not be questioned in any other Place.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Restrictions on Holding Civil Office\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Prohibition on Appointment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Senator or Representative shall, during the Time for which they were elected, be appointed to any civil Office under the Authority of the Federation, which shall have been created, or the Emoluments whereof shall have been increased during such time.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Prohibition on Simultaneous Office-Holding \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person holding any Office under the Federation shall be a Member of either Chamber during their Continuance in Office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 8: Legislative Process\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Revenue Bills\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 All Bills for raising Revenue shall originate in the House of Representatives; provided, however, that the Senate may propose or concur with Amendments as on other Bills.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Enactment of Legislation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Passage by Both Chambers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Bill which shall have passed the House of Representatives and the Senate and been approved by a simple majority in the Public Square shall, before it becomes a Law, be presented to the Premier of Earth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Premier's Action \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 If the Premier approves the Bill, they shall sign it, and it shall become Law; If the Premier does not approve the Bill, they shall return it, with their Objections, to the Chamber in which it originated.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Reconsideration After Veto \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Chamber of origin shall enter the Premier's Objections at large on its Journal and proceed to reconsider the Bill; If, after Reconsideration, two-thirds (2/3) of that Chamber agree to pass the Bill, it shall be sent, together with the Objections, to the other Chamber; If approved by two-thirds (2/3) of the second Chamber, the Bill shall become Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Recording of Votes \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In all cases of reconsideration after a veto: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls63\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Votes of both Chambers shall be determined by Yeas and Nays.\
\ls63\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Names of the Persons voting for and against the Bill shall be entered on the Journal of each Chamber respectively.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Automatic Enactment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 If any Bill shall not be returned by the Premier within ten (10) Days (Sundays excepted) after it shall have been presented to them, the Same shall become Law, as if the Premier had signed it, unless the World Congress by their Adjournment prevent its Return, in which Case it shall not become Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Orders, Resolutions, and Votes\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Presentation to Premier \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Every Order, Resolution, or Vote to which the Concurrence of the Senate and House of Representatives may be necessary (except on a question of Adjournment) shall be presented to the Premier of Earth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Approval Process \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Before taking Effect, such Order, Resolution, or Vote shall be approved by the Premier; If disapproved by the Premier, it shall be repassed by two-thirds (2/3) of the Senate and House of Representatives, according to the Rules and Limitations prescribed in the Case of a Bill.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 9: Powers Vested in the World Congress\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Enumerated Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The World Congress shall be vested with the following powers:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Taxation and Fiscal Powers \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls64\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone To lay and collect Taxes, including but not limited to Income Taxes from any source derived, Duties, Imposts, and Excises, without regard to any census or enumeration, for the purposes of debt repayment, provision of common defense, and promotion of the general welfare of Earth; provided, however, that all Duties, Imposts, and Excises shall be uniform throughout Earth;\
\ls64\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone To borrow Money on the credit of Earth;\
\ls64\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone To establish and maintain an Federal Reserve System;\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Commerce and Infrastructure \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls65\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone To regulate Commerce with extraterrestrial entities;\
\ls65\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone To regulate the Internet and all forms of Infrastructure;\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Naturalization and Bankruptcy \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls66\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone To establish uniform Rules of Naturalization and uniform Laws on Bankruptcies throughout Earth;\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Currency and Measurements \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls67\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(g)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone To coin Money, regulate the Value thereof, and of foreign Currency; \
\ls67\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(h)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone To establish and maintain the Metric System as the standard for Weights and Measures;\
