Subsection 1: Prohibition on Restriction \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall not prohibit the migration or immigration of Persons whom existing Nations have agreed to admit.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Taxation Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Notwithstanding Subsection 1, the World Congress may impose a tax or duty not exceeding ten (10) credits per Person admitted.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Suspension of Habeas Corpus and Declaration of Martial Law\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: General Prohibition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The privilege of the Writ of Habeas Corpus shall not be suspended, nor shall Martial Law be declared, except as provided for in this Section.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Conditions for Suspension or Declaration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The suspension of Habeas Corpus or declaration of Martial Law may only occur when: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls78\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone There is a state of Rebellion against the lawful government of the Federation or any of its member Nations; or \
\ls78\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone There is an Invasion by foreign powers; and\
\ls78\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The public Safety demonstrably requires such action.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Authority to Suspend or Declare \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Only the Premier, with the concurrence of two-thirds of the World Congress, may suspend the Writ of Habeas Corpus or declare Martial Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Territorial Limitations \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any suspension of Habeas Corpus or declaration of Martial Law shall be limited to the specific geographic areas affected by the Rebellion or Invasion.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Duration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The initial period of suspension or declaration shall not exceed thirty (30) days; Extensions may be granted by the World Congress in thirty (30) day increments, each requiring a two-thirds majority vote.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Judicial Review \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Star Court shall have the power to review the legality and necessity of any suspension of Habeas Corpus or declaration of Martial Law; Such review may be initiated by any affected party or by the Court sua sponte.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Rights During Suspension or Martial Law \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Even during periods of suspended Habeas Corpus or Martial Law: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls79\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to life shall remain inviolable;\
\ls79\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The prohibition against torture shall remain absolute;\
\ls79\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The right to due process shall be maintained to the greatest extent possible.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 8: Compensation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any person detained under a suspension of Habeas Corpus who is later found to be innocent shall be entitled to compensation as prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 9: Restoration of Civil Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Civil authority shall be restored as soon as the conditions necessitating the suspension or declaration no longer exist.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 10: Accountability \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 At the conclusion of any period of suspended Habeas Corpus or Martial Law, a full report must be submitted to the World Congress and made public, detailing the actions taken and their justifications.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Prohibition of Ex Post Facto Laws and Bills of Attainder\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Ex Post Facto Laws \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Law shall be enacted that: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls80\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Criminalizes an action retroactively;\
\ls80\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Aggravates a crime, or makes it greater than it was, when committed;\
\ls80\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Changes the punishment, or inflicts a greater punishment, than the Law annexed to the crime when committed;\
\ls80\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Alters the legal rules of evidence, and receives less, or different, testimony, than the Law required at the time of the commission of the offense, to convict the offender.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Bills of Attainder \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Law shall be enacted that: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls81\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Declares a person or group of persons guilty of a crime without a trial;\
\ls81\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Imposes punishment without judicial proceedings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Scope of Prohibition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This prohibition shall apply to all levels of government within the Federation, including National and local governments.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Exceptions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Laws that decriminalize actions or reduce punishments may be applied retroactively; This Section shall not be construed to prohibit the enactment of laws that have incidental retroactive effects, provided their primary purpose is not punitive.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Judicial Review \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Star Court and inferior courts shall have the power to strike down any Law that violates the prohibitions in this Section.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Remedies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any person convicted or punished under a Law that violates this Section shall have the right to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls82\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Immediate release if imprisoned;\
\ls82\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Expungement of the conviction from their record;\
\ls82\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Compensation for any penalties or damages incurred as a result of the unconstitutional Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Legislative Responsibility \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress and National legislatures shall review existing laws to ensure compliance with this Section and shall repeal or amend any laws found to be in violation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 8: Public Education \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall ensure that the principles and importance of the prohibitions in this Section are included in civic education programs.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Restrictions on Taxation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Direct Taxes \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Capitation, or other direct, Tax shall be laid, unless in Proportion to the Census or Enumeration herein before directed to be taken.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Export Taxes \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Tax or Duty shall be laid on Articles exported from any Nation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Commerce and Revenue Regulations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: No Preference Among Ports \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Preference shall be given by any Regulation of Commerce or Revenue to the Ports of one Nation over those of another.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: International Commerce \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Vessels bound to, or from, one Nation, shall not be obliged to enter, clear, or pay Duties in another.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Treasury Withdrawals and Fiscal Reporting\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Authorized Withdrawals \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Money shall be drawn from the Treasury, but in Consequence of Appropriations made by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Public Reporting \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A regular Statement and Account of the Receipts and Expenditures of all public Money shall be published at intervals prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section G: Titles of Nobility and Foreign Emoluments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Prohibition on Titles of Nobility \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Title of Nobility shall be granted by the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Foreign Emoluments \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person holding any Office under the Federation shall, without the Consent of the World Congress, accept any present, Emolument, Office, or Title, of any kind whatever, from any Sovereign, extraterrestrial State, or extraterrestrial entity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa427\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs51\fsmilli25740 \cf3 Chapter III \'96 Supreme Executive\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf3 Article 1: Executive Authority\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Vesting of Executive Power\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Supreme Executive Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The executive Power of Earth shall be vested in a singular supreme executive authority, hereinafter referred to as the "Premier of Earth."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Scope of Executive Power \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The executive Power vested in the Premier of Earth shall extend to all matters within the jurisdiction of the Federation, as defined and limited by this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Administration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier of Earth shall be assisted in the execution of their duties by an Administration, the composition and structure of which shall be as prescribed by Law enacted by the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Delegation of Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier may, in accordance with this Constitution and Laws enacted pursuant thereto, delegate specific executive functions to members of their Administration or other subordinate officers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Responsibility \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Notwithstanding any delegation under Subsection 4, the Premier shall remain ultimately responsible for the exercise of all executive Powers vested by this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Limitations \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The executive Power shall be exercised in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this Constitution and the Laws of Earth enacted pursuant thereto.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Term of Office and Election\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Duration of Term \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier, together with the Vice Premier, shall hold their Offices for a Term of four (4) years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Term Limitations \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be elected to the Office of the Premier more than twice (2); No Person who has held the Office of Premier, or acted as Premier, for more than two (2) years of a term to which some other Person was elected Premier shall be elected to the Office of the Premier more than once (1).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Qualifications for Office\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Citizenship Requirement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person, except a natural born Citizen of Earth at the time of the Adoption of this Constitution, shall be eligible for the Office of Premier.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Age and Residency Requirements \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be eligible for the Office of Premier unless they: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls83\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Have attained the age of thirty-five (35) years;\
\ls83\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Have not exceeded the age of sixty-five (65) years; and\
\ls83\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Were born on Earth; and \
\ls83\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Have been a Resident on Earth for an aggregate period of not less than fourteen (14) years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Compensation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Remuneration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier shall, at stated Times, receive for their Services, a Compensation, which shall neither be increased nor diminished during the Period for which they shall have been elected.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Prohibition on Additional Emoluments \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier shall not receive within their Term of Office any other Emolument from Earth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Oath of Office\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 Prior to assuming the Duties of the Office, the Premier-elect shall take the following Oath or Affirmation:\
"I do solemnly swear (or affirm) that I will faithfully execute the Office of Premier of Earth, and will to the best of my Ability, preserve, protect and defend the Constitution of Earth."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 2: Election of the Premier and Vice Premier\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Electoral Process\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Method of Election \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier and Vice Premier shall be elected jointly by a direct, popular vote of all eligible members of the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Voting System\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Ranked-Choice Voting \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The election shall utilize a ranked-choice voting system, as prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Winning Threshold\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Majority Requirement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 To be elected, a ticket must receive a majority (more than 50%) of the valid votes cast.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Runoff Provision \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 If no ticket receives a majority in the initial round of voting, a runoff shall be conducted between the two tickets receiving the highest number of votes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Implementation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Congressional Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall have the power to enact legislation to implement and oversee this electoral process, ensuring its integrity, security, and accessibility to all eligible voters in the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Election Date\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Determination of Election Day \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, determine the time of the Election for Premier and Vice Premier, and shall designate the Day on which the Members of the Public Square shall cast their Votes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Uniformity Requirement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Election Day shall be uniform throughout the Federation. No Nation shall conduct the Election on any Day other than that prescribed by the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Duration of Voting Period\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Extended Voting Period \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Notwithstanding Section E, the World Congress may, by Law, establish a voting period not to exceed seven (7) Earth days, to accommodate the diverse time zones and circumstances of the global populace.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Simultaneous Commencement and Conclusion \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The commencement and conclusion of the voting period established under Subsection 1 shall be simultaneous across all Nations of the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section G: Certification of Results\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Procedural Requirements \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish procedures for the timely tabulation, verification, and certification of Election results from all Nations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Integrity and Transparency \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The procedures established under Subsection 1 shall ensure the integrity and transparency of the electoral process.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 3: Succession and Contingency\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Line of Succession\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Devolution of Powers and Duties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In the event of the Removal of the Premier from Office, or of their Death, Resignation, or Inability to discharge the Powers and Duties of the said Office, the Same shall devolve on the Vice Premier.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Vacancy in the Office of Vice Premier \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Whenever there is a vacancy in the office of the Vice Premier, the Premier shall nominate a Vice Premier who shall take office upon confirmation by a majority vote of both Chambers of the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Simultaneous Vacancies in Offices of Premier and Vice Premier \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In the event of simultaneous vacancies in the offices of both the Premier and Vice Premier, the President of the Senate shall immediately assume the office of Acting Premier, and the Speaker of the House of Representatives shall immediately assume the office of Acting Vice Premier; The Acting Premier and Acting Vice Premier shall discharge the powers and duties of their respective offices until such time as duly elected successors take office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Special Elections\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Upon the occurrence of simultaneous vacancies as described in Subsection 3, special elections shall be held within ninety (90) days to fill the offices of Premier and Vice Premier for the remainder of the original term; The World Congress shall, by Law, provide for the conduct of such special elections.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Vacancies in Legislative Leadership Positions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Upon the elevation of the President of the Senate to Acting Premier, the Senate shall immediately elect a new President of the Senate; Upon the elevation of the Speaker of the House of Representatives to Acting Vice Premier, the House of Representatives shall immediately elect a new Speaker; The elections shall take place within seventy-two (72) hours of the respective elevations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Limitation on Succession \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No person constitutionally ineligible to the office of Premier shall serve as Acting Premier or Acting Vice Premier.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Voluntary Declaration of Inability\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Transmission of Declaration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Whenever the Premier transmits to the Vice Prime Senator of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of Representatives their written declaration that they are unable to discharge the powers and duties of their office, such powers and duties shall be discharged by the Vice Premier as Acting Premier.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Resumption of Powers and Duties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier shall resume the powers and duties of their office upon transmitting to the aforementioned officials a written declaration to the contrary.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Involuntary Declaration of Inability\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Declaration by Vice Premier and Cabinet \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Whenever the Vice Premier and a majority of either: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls84\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone the principal officers of the executive departments, or \
\ls84\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Such other body as the World Congress may by Law provide, transmit to the President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of Representatives their written declaration that the Premier is unable to discharge the powers and duties of their office, the Vice Premier shall immediately assume the powers and duties of the office as Acting Premier.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Contestation by Premier \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier may transmit to the President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of Representatives their written declaration that no inability exists, whereupon they shall resume the powers and duties of their office; The Premier shall not resume if, within four (4) days of the Premier's declaration, the Vice Premier and a majority of either the principal officers of the executive departments or of such other body as the World Congress may by Law provide, transmit to the President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of Representatives their written declaration that the Premier is unable to discharge the powers and duties of their office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Congressional Determination \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Upon receipt of a declaration under Subsection 2(b), the World Congress shall assemble within forty-eight (48) hours if not in session. The World Congress shall decide the issue within twenty-one (21) days of: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls85\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Receipt of the written declaration, or\
\ls85\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The date on which the World Congress is required to assemble, if not in session.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0
\cf3 If the World Congress, by two-thirds (2/3) vote of both Chambers, determines that the Premier is unable to discharge the powers and duties of their office, the Vice Premier shall continue to discharge the same as Acting Premier; otherwise, the Premier shall resume the powers and duties of their office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 \page Article 4: Military Command and Executive Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Commander-in-Chief\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Premier shall be Supreme Commander-in-Chief of the Army, Navy, Air Force, and Space Force of Earth, and of the Militia of the many Nations when called into the actual Service of Earth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Executive Consultation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Premier may require, in writing, the Opinion of the principal Officer in each of the executive Departments, upon any Subject relating to the Duties of their respective Positions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Clemency Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Premier shall have Power to grant Reprieves and Pardons for Offenses against the Federation, except in Cases of Impeachment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Treaty and Appointment Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Treaties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier shall have Power, by and with the Advice and Consent of the Senate, to make Treaties, provided two-thirds (2/3) of the Senators present concur.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Appointments \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier shall nominate, and by and with the Advice and Consent of the Senate, shall appoint Ambassadors, other public Ministers and Consuls, Judges of the Star Court, and all other Officers of Earth, whose Appointments are not herein otherwise provided for, and which shall be established by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Congressional Delegation of Appointment Power \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress may by Law vest the Appointment of such inferior Officers, as they think proper, in the Premier alone, in the Courts of Law, or in the Heads of Departments.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Recess Appointments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Premier shall have Power to fill up all Vacancies that may happen during the Recess of the Senate, by granting Commissions which shall expire at the End of their next Session.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 5: Federal Security Council\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Establishment and Composition\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Creation of the Council \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 There is hereby established an Federal Security Council (hereinafter referred to as "the Council") to advise the Premier on matters of global security and to execute certain powers as enumerated in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Composition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Council shall consist of fifteen (15) members, all of whom shall be Heads of State of Nations within the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Appointment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier shall appoint the members of the Council, subject to the following conditions: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls86\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Appointments shall reflect a geographically balanced representation of the Federation;\
\ls86\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone No more than one representative from any Nation may serve on the Council simultaneously;\
\ls86\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Appointments shall be made with due consideration to the military, economic, and diplomatic capabilities of the Nations represented.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Terms of Office\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Duration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Members of the Council shall serve for terms of two (2) years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Rotation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish a system of rotation to ensure regular turnover in Council membership while maintaining continuity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Reappointment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Council members may be reappointed for non-consecutive terms, with no Head of State serving more than two terms in total.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Powers and Responsibilities\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Advisory Function \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Council shall advise the Premier on matters relating to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls87\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The maintenance of international peace and security; \
\ls87\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Global crisis management and response; \
\ls87\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Counterterrorism and transnational crime; \
\ls87\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Nuclear non-proliferation and disarmament; \
\ls87\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Cybersecurity and emerging technological threats; \
\ls87\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Climate security and environmental crises.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Decision-Making Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Council shall have the power to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls88\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Determine the existence of any threat to global peace and security;\
\ls88\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Recommend appropriate measures to restore international peace and security; \
\ls88\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Call upon Nations to implement specific sanctions or other measures short of the use of armed force.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Use of Force \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any decision regarding the use of armed force shall require: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls89\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A unanimous vote of the Council; and \
\ls89\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Subsequent approval by a two-thirds majority of the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Procedures\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Meetings \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Council shall  meet regularly as determined by its rules of procedure, and may be convened for emergency sessions at the request of the Premier or any Council member.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Voting \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each member of the Council shall have one vote. Decisions on procedural matters shall be made by an affirmative vote of nine members. Decisions on all other matters shall be made by an affirmative vote of twelve members.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Recusal \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Members shall recuse themselves from voting on matters directly involving their own Nation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Accountability and Transparency\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Reporting \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Council shall submit annual reports, and special reports as necessary, to the World Congress on its activities and decisions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Public Access \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The proceedings of the Council shall be made public, except when the Council determines that classified information must be protected for reasons of global security.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Relationship with Other Organs\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: World Congress \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Council shall work in close cooperation with the World Congress, particularly on matters requiring legislative action or budgetary allocations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Star Court \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Decisions of the Council may be subject to judicial review by the Star Court to ensure compliance with this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 6: Executive Interaction with the World Congress\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: State of the Union and Legislative Recommendations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Premier shall periodically present reports to the World Congress on the State of the Union and recommend for their Consideration such Measures as the Premier shall judge necessary and expedient.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Convening and Adjourning Congress\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Convening Congress \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 On extraordinary Occasions, the Premier may convene both Chambers, or either of them.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Adjourning Congress \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In Case of Disagreement between the Chambers, with Respect to the Time of Adjournment, the Premier may adjourn them to such Time as the Premier shall think proper.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Reception of Ambassadors\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Premier shall receive Ambassadors and other public Ministers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Execution of Laws\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Premier shall take Care that the Laws be faithfully executed, and shall Commission all the Officers of the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 7: Impeachment and Removal\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Grounds for Removal\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Premier, Vice Premier, and all civil Officers of Earth, shall be removed from Office on Impeachment for, and Conviction of, Treason, Bribery, or other high Crimes and Misdemeanors.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Procedure\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The procedure for Impeachment and Removal shall be as prescribed elsewhere in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa427\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs51\fsmilli25740 \cf3 Chapter IV \'96 Global Judiciary\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf3 Article 1: Judicial Power and Jurisdiction\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Establishment of Courts\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Vesting of Judicial Power \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The judicial Power of Earth shall be vested in one (1) supreme global judiciary, hereinafter referred to as the "Star Court," and in such inferior Courts as the World Congress may from time to time ordain and establish.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Limitation on Jurisdiction \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The judicial Power shall not be construed to extend to any suit in Law or equity, commenced or prosecuted against a Citizen of Earth by Citizens of any Alien Nation, or by Citizens or Subjects of any Alien Species.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Scope of Judicial Power\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Extent of Jurisdiction \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The judicial Power shall extend to all Cases, in Law and Equity, arising under: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls90\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone This Constitution; \
\ls90\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Laws of Earth; and\
\ls90\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Treaties made, or which shall be made, under the Authority of the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Specific Jurisdictional Grants \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The judicial Power shall further extend to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls91\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone All Cases affecting Ambassadors, other public Senators and Consuls;\
\ls91\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone All Cases of admiralty and maritime Jurisdiction;\
\ls91\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Controversies to which the Federation shall be a Party;\
\ls91\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Controversies between two or more Nations;\
\ls91\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Controversies between a Nation and Citizens of another Nation;\
\ls91\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Controversies between Citizens of different Nations;\
\ls91\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(g)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Controversies between Citizens of the same Nation claiming Lands under Grants of different Nations; and\
\ls91\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(h)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Controversies between a Nation, or the Citizens thereof, and extraterrestrial Species, Citizens or Subjects.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Original and Appellate Jurisdiction\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Original Jurisdiction of the Star Court \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In all Cases affecting Ambassadors, other public Senators and Consuls, and those in which a Nation shall be Party, the Star Court shall have original Jurisdiction.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Appellate Jurisdiction of the Star Court \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In all other Cases mentioned in Section B, the Star Court shall have appellate Jurisdiction, both as to Law and Fact, with such Exceptions, and under such Regulations as the World Congress shall make.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Trial by Jury\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Requirement of Jury Trial \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Trial of all Crimes, except in Cases of Impeachment, shall be by Jury.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Venue \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Such Trial shall be held in the Nation where the said Crimes shall have been committed; but when not committed within any Nation, the Trial shall be at such Place or Places as the World Congress may by Law have directed.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 2: Composition of the Star Court\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Number of Justices\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Minimum and Maximum \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Star Court shall be composed of no fewer than nine (9) Justices and no more than nineteen (19) Justices.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Determination of Number \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The precise number of Justices within the range specified in Subsection 1 shall be determined by Law enacted by the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Chief Justice\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Requirement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 At all times, at least one (1) member of the Star Court shall hold the office of Chief Justice.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Associate Justices\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Designation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All Justices of the Star Court other than the Chief Justice shall be designated as Associate Justices.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Appointment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Nomination \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Premier shall nominate candidates for all vacancies on the Star Court, including the position of Chief Justice.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Confirmation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Nominees shall be confirmed by a two-thirds (2/3) majority vote of the Senate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Qualifications\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Eligibility Criteria \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 To be eligible for appointment to the Star Court, a person must: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls92\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Be at least forty (40) years of age;\
\ls92\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Have been a citizen of the Federation for at least fifteen (15) years;\
\ls92\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Have demonstrated exceptional legal acumen and integrity;\
\ls92\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Have served with distinction in high judicial office in a Nation of the Federation, or as a jurist of recognized competence in international Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Diversity Consideration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In nominating and confirming Justices, due consideration shall be given to ensuring that the composition of the Star Court reflects the diversity of legal systems and geographic regions within the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Vacancy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Filling Vacancies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In the event of a vacancy on the Star Court, the position shall be filled in accordance with the appointment process outlined in Section D of this Article.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Interim Measures \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, provide for the temporary execution of the duties of a vacant Justice position until such time as the vacancy is filled.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 3: Judicial Tenure and Compensation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Term of Office\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Duration of Judicial Appointments \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Judges, both of the Star Court and inferior Courts established pursuant to this Constitution, shall hold their Offices for a Term of sixteen (16) years from the date of their appointment and qualification.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Commencement of Term \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Term of Office specified in Subsection 1 shall commence upon the Judge taking the oath of office as prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Judicial Compensation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Entitlement to Compensation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Judges shall, at stated Times as prescribed by Law, receive for their Services a Compensation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Prohibition on Diminution \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Compensation referred to in Subsection 1 shall not be diminished during a Judge's Continuance in Office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Periodic Review \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish a mechanism for the periodic review and adjustment of Judicial Compensation to ensure its adequacy and maintain the independence of the Judiciary.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Removal and Discipline\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Removal from Office \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Judges may be removed from Office only for reasons of incapacity, misconduct, or neglect of duty, and only by the process of impeachment as prescribed elsewhere in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Disciplinary Measures \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish a system for the discipline of Judges for conduct not warranting removal, which shall be administered by the Judiciary itself to preserve its independence.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Retirement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Mandatory Retirement Age \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Judges shall retire from active service upon reaching the age of sixty-five (65) years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Senior Status \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress may, by Law, provide for Judges who have reached the mandatory retirement age to assume senior status, allowing them to continue to perform judicial duties on a limited basis.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 \page Article 4: Restraints and Limitations on Judicial Review\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Scope of Judicial Review\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Constitutional Basis \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Star Court and such inferior courts as established by Law shall have the power of judicial review to determine the constitutionality of acts of the World Congress, the Premier, and the Nations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Limitation to Cases and Controversies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The power of judicial review shall be exercised only in the context of actual cases and controversies properly brought before the courts.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Principles of Judicial Restraint\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Presumption of Constitutionality \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All acts of the World Congress, the Premier, and the Nations shall be presumed constitutional unless clearly repugnant to this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Avoidance of Constitutional Questions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The courts shall, where possible, resolve cases on non-constitutional grounds, resorting to constitutional adjudication only when absolutely necessary to resolve the dispute at hand.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Narrow Rulings \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 When engaging in constitutional adjudication, the courts shall strive to issue rulings that are as narrow and limited as possible to resolve the specific dispute before them.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Political Question Doctrine\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Non-Justiciable Political Questions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The courts shall refrain from deciding political questions that are more appropriately resolved by the political branches of government.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Factors for Consideration \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In determining whether a matter constitutes a political question, the courts shall consider: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls93\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The text of the Constitution; \
\ls93\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The structure of the government as delineated in the Constitution;\
\ls93\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Judicial manageability of the issue;\
\ls93\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The need for finality in the political decision-making process;\
\ls93\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The proper allocation of decision-making responsibility within the government.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Deference to Legislative Findings\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Factual Determinations \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The courts shall give due deference to factual findings made by the World Congress in the course of its legislative functions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Rational Basis \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Where the World Congress has made a rational determination based on substantial evidence, the courts shall not substitute their judgment for that of the legislature.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Limitations on Remedies\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Declaratory Relief \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 When a Law or act is found unconstitutional, the primary remedy shall be declaratory relief, stating the Law or act's incompatibility with the Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Injunctive Relief \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Injunctive relief against enforcement of unconstitutional laws or acts shall be narrowly tailored and issued only when necessary to prevent irreparable harm.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Prohibition on Judicial Legislation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The courts shall not, under the guise of constitutional interpretation, engage in judicial legislation or policy-making.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Advisory Opinions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Prohibition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Star Court and inferior courts shall not issue advisory opinions on the constitutionality of proposed legislation or executive actions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Exception for Constitutional Council \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Notwithstanding Subsection 1, the World Congress may, by Law, establish a Constitutional Council within the Star Court to provide non-binding advisory opinions on the constitutionality of proposed legislation upon request of the World Congress or the Premier.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section G: Constitutional Interpretation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Principles of Interpretation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In interpreting this Constitution, the courts shall consider: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls94\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The plain meaning of the text;\
\ls94\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The original understanding of the provision at the time of adoption;\
\ls94\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The structure and purpose of the Constitution as a whole;\
\ls94\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Precedent and stare decisis;\
\ls94\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The practical consequences of a particular interpretation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Living Constitution \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 While respecting the original meaning of the Constitution, the courts may adapt their interpretation to changing societal circumstances, provided such adaptation does not contravene the fundamental principles and structures established by this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section H: Deference to Subject Matter Experts\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Requirement for Expert Testimony \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In cases involving specialized or technical knowledge, the courts shall seek and give due consideration to the testimony of relevant subject matter experts.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Fields of Expertise \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Areas requiring expert testimony may include, but are not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls95\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Scientific matters;\
\ls95\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Medical and public health issues;\
\ls95\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Technological and engineering concerns;\
\ls95\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Historical facts and interpretations;\
\ls95\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(e)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Economic and financial analyses;\
\ls95\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(f)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Environmental and ecological considerations;\
\ls95\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(g)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Psychological and sociological phenomena.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Selection of Experts \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The court shall ensure that experts are selected based on their recognized expertise, credibility, and impartiality within their respective fields.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Weighing of Expert Testimony \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 While giving due deference to expert testimony, the court shall: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls96\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Consider the consensus view within the relevant field of expertise;\
\ls96\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Evaluate the methodology and reasoning underlying expert opinions;\
\ls96\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Assess the relevance of the expert testimony to the legal issues at hand.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Conflicting Expert Opinions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Where expert opinions conflict, the court shall: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls97\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Carefully weigh the credibility and foundations of each expert's testimony;\
\ls97\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Consider the degree of consensus within the relevant scientific or professional community;\
\ls97\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Articulate clearly the reasons for preferring one expert opinion over another.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Limitations on Judicial Expertise \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The court shall refrain from substituting its own judgment for that of qualified experts in matters requiring specialized knowledge, except where expert testimony is clearly erroneous, internally inconsistent, or contrary to well-established facts.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 7: Continuing Education for Judiciary \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall establish programs for the continuing education of judges in scientific and technical matters to enhance their ability to understand and evaluate expert testimony.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 8: Amicus Curiae Briefs \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The court shall welcome and give due consideration to amicus curiae briefs from relevant scientific bodies, professional associations, and academic institutions to provide broader context and perspective on specialized issues.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 9: Transparency \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The court's reliance on or rejection of expert testimony shall be clearly articulated in its decisions, providing a reasoned explanation for its treatment of expert evidence.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa427\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs51\fsmilli25740 \cf3 \page Chapter V \'96 Universal Assembly\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf3 Article 1: Vesting of Popular Sovereignty\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Establishment of the Public Square\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Vesting of Powers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All powers inherent to the People, including but not limited to the power to elect the Premier and Vice-Premier, shall be vested in and exercised through a universal social assembly, hereinafter referred to as the "Public Square."\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Nature of the Public Square \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Public Square shall constitute the primary forum for the expression of popular will and the exercise of direct democracy within the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Scope of Authority\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Electoral Powers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Public Square shall possess and exercise the exclusive authority to elect the Premier and Vice-Premier of the Federation, in accordance with procedures established elsewhere in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Other Powers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In addition to the electoral powers specified in Subsection 1, the Public Square shall exercise such other powers as may be enumerated in this Constitution or subsequently granted by the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Inviolability\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The powers vested in the Public Square shall not be abridged, delegated, or transferred to any other body or entity, except as expressly provided for in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 \page Article 2: Composition and Operation of the Public Square\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Composition and Suffrage\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Eligibility for Participation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Public Square shall be constituted of all Inhabitants of the Nations of Earth who have attained the age of eighteen (18) years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Non-Discrimination in Voting Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The right of Citizens of Earth, having attained the age of eighteen (18) years or more, to vote shall not be denied or abridged by the Federation or by any Nation on the basis of age, sex, sexual orientation, religion, or other status, nor by reason of failure to pay any poll tax or other tax.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Electoral Mechanisms\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Allocation of Votes \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Person of Earth, upon attaining the age of eighteen (18) years, shall be entitled to one (1) vote in the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Vote Security and Verification \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All votes shall be secured and authenticated through the DigitalMe ID system, and may be cast in any Election for which the individual is a verified participant.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Formation of Voluntary Associations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Group Establishment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Voluntary associations, hereinafter referred to as "Groups," may be formed within the Public Square when a collective of like-minded individuals, numbering no fewer than two (2) Persons and no more than ten million (10,000,000) Persons, assembles and associates.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Group Recognition \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Such Groups shall petition the Federation for official recognition and license to operate within the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Recognition of Natural Associations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Definition of Natural Groups \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All marriages, civil unions, domestic partnerships, and families shall be classified as natural groups within the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Registration Requirement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All natural groups, as defined in Subsection 1, shall be registered within the DigitalMe ID system.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Leadership of the Public Square\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Selection of the Vox Populi\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Public Square shall, through processes to be established by Law, select a Vox Populi to serve as the Steward of the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Powers and Duties of the Steward\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Steward of the Public Square shall have the duty to address the World Congress annually on the State of the People; The Steward shall possess the power to call for a Convocation, subject to the procedures and limitations set forth elsewhere in this Constitution; The Steward shall be vested with the authority to oversee and maintain the Public Square; All further powers and duties of the Steward of the Public Square shall be prescribed by Law, as enacted by the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Term of Office\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Steward shall hold office for a term of eight (8) years; No person shall be elected to the office of Steward more than three (3) times; For the purposes of this Subsection, election to any portion of a term shall be deemed an election to a full term.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Method of Selection\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Steward shall be selected through a popular vote of all eligible members of the Public Square; The election shall utilize a ranked-choice voting system, as prescribed by Law; The World Congress shall, by Law, establish the procedures for conducting the election, including but not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls98\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Nomination processes;\
\ls98\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Campaign regulations;\
\ls98\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Voting procedures; and\
\ls98\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Methods for tabulation and certification of results.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Qualifications for Office\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No person shall be eligible for the office of Steward unless they meet the following qualifications:\
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls99\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone They have attained the age of eighteen (18) years;\
\ls99\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone They have not exceeded the age of forty-five (45) years at the time of election;\
\ls99\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone They are a natural born inhabitant of Earth; and\
\ls99\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone They have been physically present on Earth for at least eighteen (18) consecutive years immediately preceding their election. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0
\cf3 For the purposes of clause (d) of this Subsection, temporary absences from Earth not exceeding a total of six (6) months within the eighteen (18) year period shall not be considered a break in consecutive residency; The World Congress shall have the power to establish, by Law, procedures for verifying candidates' compliance with these qualifications.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 6: Vacancy and Succession\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In the event of a vacancy in the office of the Steward of the Public Square, whether by reason of death, resignation, removal, or inability to discharge the powers and duties of the said office, the following procedures shall apply: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls100\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Premier shall, within twenty-four (24) hours of the occurrence of the vacancy, appoint an Acting Steward to discharge the powers and duties of the office;\
\ls100\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone An election to select a new Steward shall be held within ninety (90) days of the occurrence of the vacancy;\
\ls100\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Acting Steward shall serve until a new Steward is duly elected and qualified.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0
\cf3 The election to fill a vacancy shall be conducted in accordance with the procedures set forth in Subsection 4 of this Section; A Steward elected to fill a vacancy shall serve only for the remainder of the unexpired term of their predecessor, but shall be eligible for re-election subject to the limitations set forth in Subsection 3 of this Section; The World Congress shall, by Law, provide for: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls101\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The specific powers and duties of the Acting Steward;\
\ls101\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The procedure for conducting an expedited election within the ninety (90) day timeframe;\
\ls101\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Any additional measures necessary to ensure the continuity of leadership in the Public Square during a period of vacancy.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Prohibition of Collective Voting\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Individual Nature of Voting Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Notwithstanding the recognition of Groups and Natural Associations within the Public Square, the right to vote shall be exercised solely by individuals. No Group, whether voluntary or natural as defined in Sections C and D of this Article, shall be permitted to cast votes as a collective entity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Preservation of Individual Autonomy \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Membership in any Group or Natural Association shall not impair, supersede, or otherwise affect the individual voting rights of any Person within the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Prohibition of Proxy Voting \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Person shall be permitted to cast a vote on behalf of any other Person or group of Persons, except as may be specifically provided for by Law in cases of medically proven incapacity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Penalties for Violation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish appropriate penalties for any attempt to subvert the individual nature of voting rights through collective or proxy voting mechanisms.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 3: Public Initiatives and Referendums\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Right of Initiative\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Fundamental Right \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The constituent units of the Public Square, as defined in Article 2, shall have the right to propose legislation and constitutional amendments through public initiatives.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Eligible Proposers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Initiatives may be proposed by: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls102\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A specified number of Individuals;\
\ls102\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A specified number of Families, Civil Unions, or Domestic Partnerships;\
\ls102\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A specified number of registered Groups;\
\ls102\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Any combination of the above, as prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Referendum Qualification Thresholds\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Global Population Threshold \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 To qualify for a global referendum, an initiative must gather signatures from at least 1% of the global population.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Threshold Adjustment \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish a mechanism to adjust this threshold in proportion to changes in the global population, to be reviewed every five (5) years.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Geographic Distribution \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Signatures must be gathered from citizens of at least one-third (1/3) of all Nations within the Federation; No single Nation may contribute more than 15% of the total required signatures.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Constituent Unit Participation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Signatures must represent a diverse cross-section of constituent units as defined in this Article; For initiatives proposed by Groups, the supporting Groups must collectively represent at least 5% of the global population in their membership.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Time Limit \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All required signatures must be collected within a period of twenty-four (24) months from the date of initiative registration.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Verification and Review Process\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Signature Verification \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish a robust process for verifying the authenticity of signatures, utilizing the secure digital infrastructure of the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Constitutional Review \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All qualified initiatives shall undergo a review by the Star Court to ensure compatibility with this Constitution and fundamental rights before proceeding to referendum.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Public Debate Period \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Qualified initiatives shall be subject to a mandatory public debate period in the Public Square before being put to a vote.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Voting on Referendums\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Voting Procedures \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish the procedures for voting on referendums, including but not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls103\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The use of the Public Square for voting;\
\ls103\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The duration of the voting period;\
\ls103\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The majority required for passage.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Approval Requirements \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 To be adopted, a referendum must receive: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls104\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone A majority of votes cast globally, and;\
\ls104\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Approval in a majority of Nations, as defined by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Implementation of Approved Referendums\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Binding Nature\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Referendums approved according to the process outlined in this Article shall be binding on the World Congress and all Nations of the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Implementation Timeline\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, within a reasonable time as prescribed by Law, take necessary actions to implement approved referendums.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Limitations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Constitutional Compliance\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No referendum may be proposed or adopted that would violate the Universal Rights guaranteed by this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Subject Matter Restrictions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

