Subsection 1: Membership \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Convocation shall be comprised of: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls105\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone All Members of both Chambers of the World Congress;\
\ls105\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Premier and Vice Premier of Earth;\
\ls105\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Steward of the Public Square; and\
\ls105\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The Justices of the Star Court, assembled in plenary session.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Leadership\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Co-Chairs \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of Representatives shall jointly preside over Convocation as co-chairs of the Unified Government.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 \page Article 2: Convening of Convocation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Extraordinary Circumstances\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Criteria for Convening \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Convocation may be convened solely under circumstances deemed extraordinary by the World Congress, including but not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls106\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Global emergencies;\
\ls106\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Catastrophic events; or\
\ls106\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Any occurrence necessitating an expedient response from the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Approval Process\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Requirements for Assembly \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The assembly of Convocation shall require: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls107\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The affirmative vote of no less than two-thirds (2/3) of the Members of both Chambers of the World Congress; and\
\ls107\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The concurrence of a simple majority of the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 3: Powers and Procedures During Convocation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Constitutional Amendments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Expedited Amendment Process \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 During the period of Convocation, amendments and revisions to this Constitution may be proposed, deliberated upon, and enacted through expedited procedures.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Approval Threshold\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Supermajority Requirement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Any amendment or revision to this Constitution proposed during Convocation shall require the affirmative vote of no less than two-thirds (2/3) of all Members present and voting for passage and ratification.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Expedited Exercise of Constitutional Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Accelerated Procedures \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All functions, duties, and powers vested in the branches of government by this Constitution may be exercised with immediacy and through accelerated procedures for the duration of Convocation, subject to such rules as Convocation may adopt.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Limitation of Expedited Powers \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The exercise of powers under this Section shall not contravene the fundamental principles of this Constitution or infringe upon the inalienable rights guaranteed herein.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 4: Termination of Convocation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Conditions for Termination\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Resolution of Circumstances \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The period of Convocation shall terminate upon the resolution of the extraordinary circumstances that necessitated its convening.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Voluntary Termination \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Notwithstanding Subsection 1, Convocation may be terminated by a vote of two-thirds (2/3) of the Members present and voting.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Primacy of Termination \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Termination shall occur upon whichever event described in Subsections 1 or 2 occurs first.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 5: Mandatory Citizen Participation During Convocation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Obligatory Engagement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Scope of Mandatory Participation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 During the period of Convocation, all Citizens of Earth who have attained the age of majority shall be required to participate in all electoral processes, including but not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls108\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Snap elections; \
\ls108\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Referendums;\
\ls108\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Constitutional amendment ratifications; and\
\ls108\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(d)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Any other matters put forth for public decision by Convocation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Voting Mechanism\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Electronic Voting \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All voting shall be conducted through the DigitalMe ID system or such other secure electronic means as may be prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Information Dissemination \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Public Square shall be utilized for the dissemination of information pertaining to the matters subject to vote.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Time Frame for Voting\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Duration of Voting Period \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Citizens shall be afforded no less than twenty-four (24) hours and no more than thirty-six (36) hours to cast their votes on any given matter, as determined by Convocation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Communication of Voting Period \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The precise duration of the voting period shall be clearly communicated to all Citizens at the commencement of each voting event.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Exemptions from Mandatory Participation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Grounds for Exemption \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Exemptions from mandatory participation may be granted only in cases of: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls109\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Severe illness or incapacitation;\
\ls109\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Extreme circumstances that prevent access to voting mechanisms; or\
\ls109\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Other situations as may be prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Verification of Exemptions \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All claims for exemption shall be subject to verification and approval by the appropriate authorities.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Penalties for Non-Compliance\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Imposition of Penalties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Failure to participate without a duly approved exemption shall result in penalties as prescribed by Law.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Nature of Penalties \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Such penalties may include, but are not limited to: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls110\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Fines;\
\ls110\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Mandatory community service; or\
\ls110\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Temporary suspension of certain non-essential Citizen privileges.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Education and Accessibility\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Provision of Information \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Convocation shall ensure that comprehensive, impartial information regarding all matters subject to vote is made readily available to all Citizens through the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Accessibility Measures \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Provisions shall be made to ensure accessibility for Citizens with disabilities or other special needs.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa427\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs51\fsmilli25740 \cf3 Chapter VII 
\fs49\fsmilli24740 \cf3 \'96
\fs51\fsmilli25740 \cf3  Constitutional Dynamics and Open Governance\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf3 Article 1: Constitutional Amendments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Proposal of Amendments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Congressional Initiative \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 When two-thirds (2/3) of the members of each Chamber of the World Congress deem it necessary, they may propose Amendments to this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: National Legislatures' Initiative \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Upon the Application of the Legislatures of two-thirds of the many Nations, the World Congress shall call a Convention for proposing Amendments.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Ratification of Amendments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Methods of Ratification \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Amendments proposed in accordance with Section A shall be valid to all Intents and Purposes, as part of this Constitution, when ratified by the Legislatures of three-fourths (3/4) of the many Nations, or by Conventions in three-fourths (3/4) thereof, as the one or the other Mode of Ratification may be proposed by the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Limitations on Amendments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: National Consent \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Amendment which may be made prior to the Year twenty eighty (2080) shall in any Manner affect any Nation in the Federation without its Consent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Preservation of Equal Suffrage \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No Amendment shall deprive any Nation of its equal Suffrage in the Senate or House of Representatives without its Consent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Certification and Proclamation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Verification of Ratification \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Law, establish procedures for the verification and certification of the ratification of Amendments by the Nations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Proclamation of Adoption \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Upon receipt of ratifications from the requisite number of Nations, the Premier of Earth shall issue a Proclamation declaring the Amendment to be adopted and specifying the date of its entry into force.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Public Square Ratification\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Requirement for Public Approval \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Notwithstanding the provisions in Section B of this Article, any Amendment proposed and ratified as per the procedures outlined therein shall require, as a final step for adoption, the approval of two-thirds (2/3) of the eligible voters in the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Voting Process \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The vote in the Public Square shall be conducted electronically through Tome.; The voting period shall last for thirty (30) days from the date the proposed Amendment is submitted for public ratification; Each eligible voter shall have one vote per proposed Amendment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Public Information Campaign \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Prior to the commencement of voting, there shall be a mandatory sixty (60) day period for public education and debate on the proposed Amendment(s), facilitated through the Public Square.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Verification and Certification \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The results of the Public Square vote shall be verified and certified by the independent electoral commission established under Chapter I, Article 10, Section D, Subsection 1 of this Constitution; The commission shall publish the verified results within seven (7) days of the conclusion of the voting period.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 5: Effect of Public Square Vote \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 If the proposed Amendment receives the approval of two-thirds (2/3) or more of the voters in the Public Square, it shall be considered ratified and shall become part of this Constitution; If the proposed Amendment fails to receive the required two-thirds approval, it shall be considered rejected and shall not become part of this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section F: Implementation of Ratified Amendments\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Proclamation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Upon certification of the Public Square vote approving an Amendment, the Premier of Earth shall issue a Proclamation declaring the Amendment to be adopted and specifying the date of its entry into force.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Incorporation into the Constitution \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The text of the ratified Amendment shall be incorporated into the Constitution at the appropriate location, as determined by the World Congress in consultation with the Star Court.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Enacting Legislation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall have the power to enact legislation necessary for the implementation of any Amendment adopted pursuant to this Article.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 2: Constitutional Convention Procedures\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Call of the Convention\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Issuance of Call \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Upon receipt of applications from two-thirds (2/3) of the National Legislatures, or upon its own initiative as provided in Article 1, the World Congress shall issue a formal call for a Constitutional Convention.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Time and Place \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, by Resolution, specify the time and place for the Convention, which shall commence no later than one (1) year after the issuance of the call.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

