\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each Nation shall be entitled to send a number of delegates to the Convention equal to its combined total of Representatives and Senators in the World Congress.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Selection of Delegates \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The method of selecting delegates shall be determined by each Nation, provided that such method ensures fair representation of the Nation's populace.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Rules of Procedure\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Adoption of Rules \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Convention shall, as its first order of business, adopt rules of procedure by a majority vote of all delegates present and voting.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Quorum \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 A quorum for conducting business shall consist of delegates from two-thirds of the Nations represented at the Convention.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Voting \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Each delegate shall have one vote. Decisions of the Convention shall be made by a majority of delegates present and voting, unless otherwise specified in the rules of procedure.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Scope of the Convention\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Limitation to Proposed Amendments \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Convention shall be limited to considering and proposing amendments to the Constitution as specified in the applications from the National Legislatures or the World Congress's initiative.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Prohibition on Complete Revision \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Convention shall not have the authority to propose a complete revision or replacement of the existing Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Transparency and Public Participation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

