\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Notwithstanding the provisions of this Article, there shall be no derogation from the essential content of the Rights and Freedoms guaranteed by this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Emergency Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Temporary Measures \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In times of public emergency which threatens the life of the Federation or a Nation thereof, and the existence of which is officially proclaimed, the Federation or a Nation may take measures derogating from their obligations under this Constitution to the extent strictly required by the exigencies of the situation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Non-Derogable Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No derogation shall be made under Subsection 1 from Articles 1-12.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 14: Unenumerated Rights\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Retention of Rights by the People\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Non-Exhaustive Nature of Enumerated Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The enumeration in this Constitution of certain rights shall not be construed to deny or disparage other rights retained by the People.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Interpretation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This Article shall be interpreted to recognize that the People possess fundamental rights beyond those explicitly enumerated in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Legal Effect\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Constitutional Status \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Rights retained by the People pursuant to this Article shall enjoy the same legal status and protection as those explicitly enumerated in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Judicial Enforcement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Star Court and such inferior courts as established by Law shall have the authority to recognize and enforce unenumerated rights consistent with the principles set forth in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Criteria for Recognition\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Standards for Identifying Unenumerated Rights \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 In determining whether an asserted right is retained by the People under this Article, the judiciary shall consider: \
\pard\tx20\tx425\pardeftab720\li425\fi-426\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls154\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(a)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The traditions and collective conscience of the People;\
\ls154\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(b)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The fundamental values of liberty and justice that underlie this Constitution;\
\ls154\ilvl0\cf3 \cb1 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	(c)	}\cf3 \cb4 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone The evolving standards of a maturing society.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Limitation on Government Power\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Restrictive Interpretation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 This Article shall be construed as a limitation on governmental power and an affirmation of the People's retained sovereignty.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Interaction with Enumerated Rights\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Non-Derogation \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Nothing in this Article shall be construed to derogate from the rights explicitly enumerated elsewhere in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 15: Implementation and Enforcement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Legislative Authority\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Enactment Power \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall have the power to enact such legislation as may be necessary and proper for the implementation and enforcement of the rights, freedoms, and protections enumerated in this Chapter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Specific Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Establishment of Bodies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall have the authority to establish, maintain, and oversee agencies, commissions, or other bodies deemed requisite for the effective realization of the provisions herein.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Fiscal Allocations \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall have the power to allocate and appropriate funds for the purpose of giving effect to the rights and protections guaranteed under this Chapter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 3: Penalties and Remedies \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall have the authority to prescribe penalties and remedies for violations of the rights and freedoms contained in this Chapter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 4: Compliance Mechanisms \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall have the power to create mechanisms for the monitoring and evaluation of Member Nations' compliance with the provisions of this Chapter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: Binding Nature of Legislation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Applicability \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 All legislation enacted pursuant to this Article shall be binding upon all Member Nations of the Federation, subject to the provisions elsewhere in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section D: Judicial Powers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Preservation of Judicial Authority \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Nothing in this Article shall be construed as limiting the inherent power of the Star Court to interpret and apply the provisions of this Chapter in cases or controversies properly brought before it.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section E: Periodic Review\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Review Requirement \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The World Congress shall, at intervals not exceeding five (5) years, review the efficacy of legislation and bodies established under this Article.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Amendments and Reforms \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Pursuant to the review conducted under Subsection 1, the World Congress shall make such amendments or reforms as may be necessary to ensure the full realization of the rights and protections guaranteed in this Chapter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa427\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs51\fsmilli25740 \cf3 \page Chapter IX \'96 Rights of Indigenous Peoples\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf3 Article 1: Fundamental Rights and Freedoms\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Equal Rights\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Collective and Individual Rights\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples and individuals have the right to the full enjoyment, as a collective or as individuals, of all human rights and fundamental freedoms as recognized in this Constitution.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Freedom from Discrimination\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples and individuals are free and equal to all other peoples and individuals and have the right to be free from any kind of discrimination, in the exercise of their rights, in particular that based on their indigenous origin or identity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Self-Determination\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Right to Self-Determination\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to self-determination. By virtue of that right they freely determine their political status and freely pursue their economic, social and cultural development.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Right to Autonomy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples, in exercising their right to self-determination, have the right to autonomy or self-government in matters relating to their internal and local affairs, as well as ways and means for financing their autonomous functions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 2: Culture, Identity, and Traditional Practices\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Cultural Rights\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Right to Cultural Practices\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to practice and revitalize their cultural traditions and customs. This includes the right to maintain, protect and develop the past, present and future manifestations of their cultures, such as archaeological and historical sites, artifacts, designs, ceremonies, technologies and visual and performing arts and literature.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Spiritual and Religious Traditions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to manifest, practice, develop and teach their spiritual and religious traditions, customs and ceremonies; the right to maintain, protect, and have access in privacy to their religious and cultural sites; the right to the use and control of their ceremonial objects; and the right to the repatriation of their human remains.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Identity and Membership\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Right to Identity\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to determine their own identity or membership in accordance with their customs and traditions. This does not impair the right of indigenous individuals to obtain citizenship of the Nations in which they live.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Institutional Structures\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to determine the structures and to select the membership of their institutions in accordance with their own procedures.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 3: Education, Information, and Media\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Education Rights\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Educational Systems\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to establish and control their educational systems and institutions providing education in their own languages, in a manner appropriate to their cultural methods of teaching and learning.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Access to Education\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous individuals, particularly children, have the right to all levels and forms of education of the Federation without discrimination.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Media and Information\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Indigenous Media\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to establish their own media in their own languages and to have access to all forms of non-indigenous media without discrimination.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Reflection in Public Media\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall take effective measures to ensure that Federation-owned media duly reflect indigenous cultural diversity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 4: Lands, Territories, and Resources\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Rights to Lands and Resources\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Ownership and Usage\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to the lands, territories and resources which they have traditionally owned, occupied or otherwise used or acquired.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Legal Recognition\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall give legal recognition and protection to these lands, territories and resources. Such recognition shall be conducted with due respect to the customs, traditions and land tenure systems of the indigenous peoples concerned.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Conservation and Protection\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Environmental Protection\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to the conservation and protection of the environment and the productive capacity of their lands or territories and resources. The Federation shall establish and implement assistance programs for indigenous peoples for such conservation and protection, without discrimination.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Hazardous Materials\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall take effective measures to ensure that no storage or disposal of hazardous materials shall take place in the lands or territories of indigenous peoples without their free, prior and informed consent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 5: Participation and Consultation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Federation Decision-Making\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Right to Participate\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to participate in decision-making in matters which would affect their rights, through representatives chosen by themselves in accordance with their own procedures, as well as to maintain and develop their own indigenous decision-making institutions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Consultation Requirement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall consult and cooperate in good faith with the indigenous peoples concerned through their own representative institutions in order to obtain their free, prior and informed consent before adopting and implementing legislative or administrative measures that may affect them.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Development and Economic Activities\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Development Priorities\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to determine and develop priorities and strategies for exercising their right to development. In particular, indigenous peoples have the right to be actively involved in developing and determining health, housing and other economic and social programmes affecting them and, as far as possible, to administer such programmes through their own institutions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Traditional Economic Activities\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Indigenous peoples have the right to maintain and develop their political, economic and social systems or institutions, to be secure in the enjoyment of their own means of subsistence and development, and to engage freely in all their traditional and other economic activities.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 6: Implementation and Enforcement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: Federation Obligations\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Legislative Measures\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall take, in consultation and cooperation with indigenous peoples, appropriate measures, including legislative measures, to achieve the ends of this Chapter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Enforcement Mechanisms\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The Federation shall provide effective mechanisms for prevention of, and redress for, any action which has the aim or effect of depriving them of their integrity as distinct peoples, or of their cultural values or ethnic identities.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: Interpretation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 1: Minimum Standards\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 The rights recognized herein constitute the minimum standards for the survival, dignity and well-being of the indigenous peoples of the Federation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl288\slmult1\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw5
Subsection 2: Non-Diminishment Clause\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Nothing in this Chapter may be interpreted as diminishing or extinguishing the rights indigenous peoples have now or may acquire in the future.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa427\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs51\fsmilli25740 \cf3 Chapter X \'96 Emerging Challenges and Future Governance\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf3 Article 1: Artificial Intelligence Governance\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section A: AI Development and Deployment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The Federation shall regulate the development and deployment of AI systems to ensure they benefit humanity and align with human values.\
All AI systems must be designed with transparency, explainability, and accountability as core principles.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section B: AI Rights and Responsibilities\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 The legal status of AI entities shall be determined based on their level of sentience and autonomy.\
AI systems granted legal personhood shall have both rights and responsibilities commensurate with their capabilities.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 Section C: AI Ethics Board\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf3 \cb4 An AI Ethics Board shall be established to oversee AI development and provide guidance on ethical issues.\
The Board shall have the power to halt or modify AI projects that pose significant risks to humanity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf3 Article 2: Space Exploration and Colonization\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

